title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and Karo in a 1 to 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Place in microwave and cook 4 minutes on High; stir.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes more on High; add vanilla and cook 1 minute.
Add oleo and cook 1 more minute.
Add peanuts and baking soda and stir until it turns light brown.
Pour on greased baking sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes into bite size pieces.
Cover with water and boil with bouillon.
Season salt and pepper.
Boil until potatoes are cooked.
Do not drain.
Add to potatoes and juice, evaporated milk and soup.
Simmer until heated through.

title: toasted biscotti
directions: Beat eggs, gradually add sugar and oil.
Add flour, baking powder and mix well.
Add flavorings and nuts.
Dough should be soft and pliable.
Form into 5 to 6 rolls and put on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 - 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool about 15 minutes.
Cut crosswise into slices and return to oven.
Bake until golden brown.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Put a layer of crackers on bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Add 1 layer of cooked cabbage, then a layer of 1/2 can mushroom soup, followed by a layer of 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers again.
Add pepper (if desired).
Top with crushed cracker crumbs on top.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
Crackers may be crushed for layers.

title: lasagne ole
directions: Brown meat and add onion that have been sauteed in margarine. Add taco seasoning and tomato mixture (Ro-Tel and tomato sauce). Simmer.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: In a large skillet, combine the broth, butter and pepper.
Add the chicken chunks and cook over medium high heat 5 minutes, or until bubbly.
Place the biscuits evenly over the top.
Reduce the heat to low, cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with the paprika and simmer, uncovered for 10-12 minutes, or until the broth is slightly thickened.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: homemade bologna
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Mix again and mold into 2 bologna shape rolls.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours on a rack, so grease will drain off.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook vegetables in enough water to cover.
Simmer until tender.
Add your soups and water.
Add cheese (cubed) and broccoli.
Simmer until cooked through.

title: icebox rolls
directions: In small bowl, combine shortening, sugar and salt.
With wooden spoon, beat until creamy.
Add boiling water; stir until smooth.
Set aside to cool to lukewarm.
In a large bowl, sprinkle yeast over 1/2 cup warm water; stir until dissolved.
Add shortening mixture to yeast along with eggs; mix well.
Add flour alternately with 1 cup warm water, beating until smooth.
Grease top of dough.
Cover bowl tightly with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
To shape, using 1/4 of dough on floured surface, roll into 1-inch rectangle; brush with 2 tablespoons oleo.
Roll up jellyroll fashion.
With sharp knife, cut crosswise into 12 pieces.
Place cut slices down in greased muffin tins.
Cover with towel; let rise in warm place about 1 hour.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Combine margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs.
Then add flour, baking soda and baking powder, small portions at a time until blended.
Add hot coffee intermittently.
Then add cocoa, vanilla and milk.
Batter will be of a loose consistency.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for butter and chicken. Dip chicken in melted butter.
Roll chicken in crumb mixture. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli on stove with onion; drain.
Put in a casserole dish and mix with other ingredients.
Sprinkle top with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sloppy joe quickies
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil.
Add remaining ingredients, adding enough water to make desired consistency. Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve on toasted buns.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound the chicken breasts flat.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mold ham around cheese.
Roll chicken around ham; secure with toothpicks. Melt butter in pie plate for about 1 minute on High.
Mix sesame seed with bread crumbs.
Dip chicken in butter, then roll in crumb mixture.
Microwave 10 to 12 minutes on High.
Rearrange once and give dish 1/2 turn during cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serve with cheese sauce.

title: autumn pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 375° (quick mod).
Beat all ingredients together. Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: mom's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and flavoring until light and fluffy. Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: breakfast brunch
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain fat.
Beat eggs, salt, milk and mustard in bowl.
In a 9 x 13 inch pan, layer sausage, cheese and bread. Pour egg mixture over layers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 40 minutes, or until set at 350 degrees.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Mix the 2 cheeses together.
Set aside.
Put 1/2 cup browned meat in tortilla.
Add 1/3 cup cheese.
Roll tortilla and hold it closed with a toothpick.
Set in cake pan.
Pour enchilada sauce over the top. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Place in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve topped with sour cream.

title: "impossible cheesecake"
directions: Mix well the cream cheese, sugar, eggs, vanilla and Bisquick. Pour mixture in spring pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: one-step ranch bread
directions: Combine 1/2 cup softened butter or margarine with 1 packet of Hidden Valley milk recipe original Ranch salad dressing mix. Slice bread lengthwise and spread tops with butter mixture.
Place bread under broiler (or cut surface down on grill) until crispy and golden brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Melt butter; set aside.
Mix eggs, milk, bread chunks and cheese.
Then add butter and ham.
Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish lightly with butter.
Pour mixture into pan.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Do not use an aluminum pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until set in center.
Cut into 12 squares.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine first three ingredients and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: squaw corn
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in small amount of vegetable oil in skillet.
Add ground beef to this and brown (do not overcook). Drain fat.
Salt and pepper to taste and add tomato soup and water.
Cover and simmer slowly for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add corn and heat for 5 minutes more.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Mix soup, orange juice and water; pour over rice.
Roll chicken in dry soup mix.
Place on top of mixture in baking dish. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: mexican fiesta biscuit bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spread melted margarine in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Separate dough into 13 biscuits.
Snip each biscuit into eighths, using kitchen cutters.
Place biscuit pieces in large bowl.
Toss with salsa.
Spoon evenly into dish.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: italian vegetable saute
directions: Recipe may be halved or doubled.

title: shana's almond supreme cake
directions: Cream butter in mixer bowl (the first 3/4 cup butter), until light and fluffy.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually; mix well.
Stir flour with baking powder and salt (3 times).
Stir flavorings into milk. Add flour mixture to creamed mixture, alternately with the milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold gently into the batter.
Pour into 3 greased 9-inch cake pans.
Tap pans on hard surface to remove bubbles.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes, or until tests done.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes before removing to cool on wire rack.

title: date-nut pudding
directions: Combine hot water and brown sugar in large baking dish. Mix together
remaining ingredients.
Spoon batter over syrup. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli according to package directions. Arrange on bottom of oblong baking dish.
Top with cooked and diced chicken.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and soup; spread over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: truffles with chestnuts
directions: Break the chocolate into pieces and put them in a pan with two teaspoons of water.
The temperature must be very low and when chocolate is melted remove the pan (we stir continuously).
Combine the 50 gr of butter (mashed) with the two (2) yolks and mix with a spatula.
Then add the rest of butter and continue mixing.
After 10 minutes of mixing well these ingredients, add the powdered sugar, whipping cream, cognac and crushed chestnuts.
Mix very well.
Put the mixture for 3 minutes in the refrigerator.
Put the cocoa in a flat plate.
Take the mixture out of the refrigerator and start giving the shape of the truffle (round), then roll each truffle in the cocoa and cover it.
Keep truffles in the refrigerator.

title: cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to bake at 375°.
Crush graham crackers and add butter and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Pat crust into a 9-inch pan or you can use prepared graham cracker crust.
Beat eggs at high speed; gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Add softened cream cheese and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, blending in at low speed.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Scald milk.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla, then add scalded milk.
Pour this mixture into chilled raw pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 30 minutes. To test for doneness, insert a table knife in center of pie.
If it comes out clean, the pie is done.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: sweet and sour chicken over rice
directions: Spray pan.
Brown chicken.
Drain.
Combine 1/4 cup pineapple syrup, lemon juice, sugar, soy sauce, bouillon and ginger.
Add to chicken.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Pour package of Ranch dressing over broccoli and cauliflower.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Before serving, mix sour cream and mayonnaise, then mix into vegetables.
Cut the onions into small strips.
Add to other vegetables.
Keep cold until ready to eat.

title: peach cream cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
(If you use a 9-inch pie plate, use less of the batter on the bottom layer.)

title: festive punch
directions: Stir the pineapple juice and limeade concentrate together in a punch bowl until well blended. Add the ginger ale sorbet. Serve immediately. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: summerberry cooler
directions: In blender combine berries and apple juice.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Pour into pitcher and slowly stir in carbonated water.
Pour over berry ice cubes (recipe to follow) in tall chilled glasses.
Serve immediately.

title: baked fish
directions: Place fillets in a lightly oiled baking dish; sprinkle with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Dot with margarine.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes until fish flakes.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Sprinkle Jello (dry) on top and fold in.
Let stand in refrigerator until jello dissolves. Serve cold.

title: old time peppermint candy cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Blend just until combined.
Add candy.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake is done.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: mom's banana pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk and egg, stirring constantly, over medium heat, until filling thickens.
Pour over layer of bananas and wafers.
Add another layer of bananas and wafers, then filling.
Do this until filling is used up.
Top off with a layer of wafers.

title: southwestern style chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange chicken in two ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dishes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, cook and stir onion and garlic in oil until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese and ripe olives; blend well.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is hot; set aside.
Remove chicken from oven.
If necessary, using spoon, remove most of the pan juices; turn chicken over.
Pour half of sauce evenly over chicken in each dish.
Return to oven; bake for an additional 20 to 30 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and juices run clear, basting occasionally.
Sprinkle chicken with cheese.
Bake for 3 more minutes or until cheese melts.
Garnish with ripe olives.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cabbage vegetable chowder
directions: In large saucepan, melt margarine; add cabbage, onions, celery, carrots and peas.
Saute 8 minutes.
Add
corn,
milk, salt, pepper and thyme.
Reduce heat and
simmer
minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese;
stir until melted.
Makes six 1 1/3 cup servings.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs.
Mix well, add other ingredients. Pour into 2 greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Your pies will have a crust after they cook.

title: granny's recipe super dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and spread 1/2 of the crumbs in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese and margarine until smooth. Mix in powdered sugar; fold in the Cool Whip.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer broccoli,
chicken
and mushrooms in order in 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over ingredients in pan.
Then
sprinkle
croutons.
Mix
in
large
bowl:
soup, mayonnaise, lemon
juice and curry powder.	Pour over ingredients. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until lightly browned. Enjoy!

title: chicken and cheese enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine chicken, 1/2 cup of salsa and lime juice.
To remaining salsa, add beef broth and tomato paste. Stir until blended.
Pour half of sauce in an 8-inch square pan. Spoon 1/4 of chicken mix into center of tortilla.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 tablespoons of cheese over it.
Loosely roll tortillas and arrange, seam side down, over sauce in pan.
Spoon other sauce over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and red onion. Bake 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 50 calories.

title: jonathan's p.b.  and j.
directions: On one slice of bread, spread peanut butter and on other slice spread jelly.
Put slices of bread together and enjoy!

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in carrots, raisins, coconut, nuts and apple.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir into flour mixture until batter is just combined.
Spoon into well-greased muffin tins, filling to the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 large muffins.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and cranberry sauce. Mix well.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients alternately with water.
Pour into two well-greased and floured loaf pans.
(I use the small pans, and it will make 7 loaves.) Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg; beat well.
Add vanilla, flour and soda; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies; mix.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet; remove from pan right away.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix crumbs and oleo; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate. Beat 2 sticks whipped oleo, eggs and powdered sugar until firm. Spread over crumb mixture.
Next layer, put sliced bananas dipped in pineapple juice.
Top that with Cool Whip.
Top that with chopped nuts and maraschino cherries.

title: shipwreck
directions: Arrange all ingredients, except soup and water, in layers in large greased casserole dish in order given.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and water and pour over layers. Cover and bake 1 hour and 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove cover and bake another 15 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with crackers with butter and let brown.
Do not dilute soup.
Prepare a day ahead.
Easy for working mothers.

title: marinated pea salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and bring to the boil. Boil for 1 minute, then cool completely.

title: lemon curd
directions: Place the sugar, butter, lemon rind and juice, and eggs in a heavy saucepan.
Cook gently over low heat until the mixture is thick but still falls easily from a spoon. Do not boil or let the mixture separate.
Remove from heat and cool. Store in the refrigerator in a tightly covered jar or freeze.

title: apricot-cheese delight
directions: Drain and chill the fruits.
Reserve juice.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add 1 cup fruit juice.
Reserve remaining juice for topping.
Chill until slightly congealed.
Fold in fruit and marshmallows.
Pour into 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread with Fruit-Cheese Topping.

title: hal's goulash
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Chop onion and bell pepper.
Put them in melted butter and fry until onions are brown.
Then add mushrooms, steak and Worcestershire sauce. (Cut steaks into small bites.)
Simmer until meat is tender.
Add jalapenos or pepper sauce, if you wish.
Serve over rice and with a salad.

title: creamy broccoli-cauliflower bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook broccoli and cauliflower in salted water until stems are almost tender (10 to 12 minutes).
Drain. Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Beat soup and milk until smooth. Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese. Mix Bisquick and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until light brown, 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tomato-aspic salad
directions: Heat tomato juice to boiling point.
Let stand 10 minutes. Strain; add vinegar, gelatin and salt.
Stir to dissolve.
Pour into salad mold.
Chill. Unmold and serve on crispy lettuce.
Top with salad dressing.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Place in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry pudding cake
directions: Mix the sugar, flour, eggs and juice from the cherries.
Add the remaining ingredients. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in sheath pan (13 x 9-inch).

title: vinaigrette salad dressing
directions: Measure mustard into a bowl. Whisk in vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and herbs to taste. Dribble in olive oil until mixture thickens. Dribble, dribble, whisk, whisk.

title: quick pecan breakfast ring
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and milk in 2-cup glass measure. Cook on Full power for 1 to 2 minutes or until butter is melted and mixture is boiling; stir well.
Sprinkle nuts evenly in 8-cup plastic or ceramic tube dish.
Pour half of brown sugar mixture over nuts.
Arrange biscuits in dish.
Top with remaining brown sugar mixture.
Cook on Cook level 7 for 7 to 9 minutes or until top springs back when lightly pressed with finger.
Turn quarter turn halfway through cooking time.
Let stand for 2 minutes. Invert onto serving platter.
Serve immediately.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg; add sugars and cream well.
Mix in dry ingredients and vanilla.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate (batter will be thick).
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: melt-in-the-mouth cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugars, oil, vanilla and eggs. Add dry ingredients.
On lightly greased cookie sheet, drop by spoonful, flatten and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon or let stand overnight in refrigerator and roll in balls.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon or colored sugar, then flatten. Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a large pot, saute onions in butter or margarine until done. Add chicken broth to onions.
Cut the very lower ends off broccoli stalks and discard.
Place broccoli in pot and cook until done. Smoosh broccoli until it has broken up in small pieces.
Add milk and half and half.
Cook approximately 45 minutes more, stirring occasionally.
Add Velveeta, cook until melted, stirring more. Thicken with cornstarch and water mixed together (approximately 2 tablespoons cornstarch).
Serve hot.

title: chocolate bar pie
directions: Put the marshmallows and chocolate bar in top of double boiler with 1/2 cup milk. Stir while mixture is melting and turning into a delectable good. When melted, remove from heat and cool. While it is cooling, make graham cracker crust and bake in oven 6 minutes at 375°. When the chocolate mixture and pie crust have cooled sufficiently, whip the cream and fold into the cooled chocolate mixture. Pour into graham cracker crust. Will be a little soupy until mixture firms up. Place in refrigerator and chill for a couple of hours before serving.

title: quick pizza dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and Italian seasonings with electric mixer on medium until blended.
Spread on 9-inch pie plate.
Top with cheese, pizza sauce, additional cheese and peppers.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until the mixture is thoroughly heated and the cheese is melted.
Serve with breadsticks.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Do not cook chicken and broccoli completely as it will finish while baking.
Set aside precooked chicken and broccoli and bread crumbs.
Mix other ingredients together.
Layer chicken and broccoli in buttered baking dish, putting the mixture on each layer.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper. Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Drain pineapple.
Reserve about 1/2 cup liquid.
Combine liquid 57 Sauce and honey; pour over chicken.
Bake additional 25 minutes, basting occasionally. Arrange some pineapple slices over chicken and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine cheese, bread crumbs and butter. Coat chicken breast with mustard, then dip in crumb mixture. Place breaded chicken in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until chicken is done. Makes 6 servings.

title: kosher-style dill pickles
directions: Pack small cucumbers into quart jars.
To each jar, add 1 teaspoon pickling spice. Add 6 to 8 garlic cloves, unpeeled and sliced in a few places.
Add 2 sprigs dill weed.
If you like, you can add 4 to 6 dried red chili peppers to each jar.
Add 3 to 4 ounces of white vinegar.
Fill a measuring cup with hot top water to dissolve 1 teaspoon salt.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour salt water in jar, cup full by cup full.
Process completed jars in water bath for minutes.
Cover and leave on table 2 days.
Now ready to eat.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Cook the package of butterscotch pudding as directed.
When thickened and while still hot, add package of butter brickle cake mix and stir in thoroughly.
Spread in a lightly greased and floured large oblong pan.
Sprinkle 1 small package of butterscotch bits over the top and add chopped walnuts.

title: smothered chops
directions: Rinse pork chops, then season with salt, pepper and celery seed. Lightly coat both sides of chops with mustard, then flour both sides. Pour both cans of soup into a pot, along with 2 cans of water. Allow to come to a boil. Brown chops in a skillet, then place chops into pot with the soup. Allow chops to simmer in the soup for an hour or until tender. Add noodles to soup/chops mixture after first 15 minutes of simmering is completed. Serve over rice.

title: church cookies
directions: First Layer:
Combine margarine, 2 cups flour and one cup brown sugar.
Mix well and spread on cookie sheet; bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until well blended.
Pour into crust and chill.
Garnish with walnuts, strawberries or pineapple, if desired.

title: ranch mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and wash about 8 large potatoes. Cut into chunks.
Place in 8-quart pan and cover with water; bring to a boil.
Boil about 20 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Drain potatoes and stir in 1/2 cup margarine and 1/2 cup milk.
Mash potatoes or use an electric mixer.
Add Hidden Valley Ranch mix.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Milnot and butter together.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir frequently.
Boil this mixture for 5 minutes.
Don't forget to stir.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Stir ingredients until mixture is creamy and smooth.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan. Allow to cool as desired.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Mix everything together in a large bowl.
Put in 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Reduce to 300° and bake an additional 45 minutes. Cool 10 minutes and remove.

title: hearty italian bean soup
directions: About 45 minutes before serving:
Cut ham into 1/2-inch pieces.
Dice celery.
Thinly slice carrots.
Chop onion.
Dice zucchini.
Remove 1 1/2 cups of white kidney beans to a medium bowl.
With potato masher or fork, mash beans until smooth.

title: banana chocolate shake
directions: In an electric blender, combine milk, yogurt, banana, chocolate syrup and sugar if desired. Blend until smooth, about 30 seconds. Serve immediately or refrigerate in a covered container. Stir before serving. Yields 3 servings.

title: autumn apricot bars("cookie")
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in rolled oats and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat 2/3 of crumb mixture into 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Spread with preserves. Cover with remaining crumb mixture.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Combine
cucumbers, onions and salt.
Stir; let stand 2 hours. Wash and drain.
Add 1/2 cup white vinegar and 1/2 cup sugar; stir
well.
Let
stand 10 minutes, then put in freezer bags or containers and put in freezer.

title: s'more cookies
directions: In 3-quart mixing bowl, combine oleo, sugar, flour and cracker crumbs.
Mix on low until particles resemble peas.
Reserve 1 1/4 cups for topping; press remainder in bottom of ungreased 9-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows over crust; place chocolate pieces over marshmallows.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until marshmallows are toasted and top is golden brown.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage (about 8 minutes).
Add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and pecans.
Mix and pour in square dish.
Cool; cut in small squares.

title: easy ham glaze
directions: Mix and boil one minute.
Baste ham with this sauce often while baking.
Makes enough glaze for a 4 pound ham.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and stir until onion is transparent. Add mushrooms and cook another 4 minutes.
Remove mixture from heat and blend in flour. Add beef stock, stirring constantly. Add bay leaf and pepper.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and stir in cream.
If desired, garnish with croutons before serving.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Put rice in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with ham, broccoli, mushrooms and cheese.
Combine the soup, mayonnaise and dry mustard; pour over ham mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Scald milk, sugar, Crisco and salt.
Stir until lukewarm.
Add yeast mix, 1 egg and 2 cups flour.
Mix and add 1 1/2 to 2 cups flour.
Mix well.
Let rise 1 to 2 hours.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip in melted butter and fold over.
Place on pan.
Let rise.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat shortening over low heat until melted; remove from heat.
Mix in brown sugar; egg and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in a greased square baking pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cut into 1 3/4-inch squares while warm.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen cookies, 120 calories each.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: In bowl combine first 7 ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown on all sides in large skillet over medium heat.
Drain off excess fat.
Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen meatballs.

title: cucumber sandwich spread
directions: Peel and finely chop the cucumber.
Combine it with the vinegar, sugar and water.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients until smooth.
May be tinted with a drop or two of food coloring, if desired.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: martha patch's buttermilk cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk until creamy and fluffy. Add vanilla.
Bake in layer cake pans at 375°.
Frost with butter icing.

title: flood pudding
directions: Break the donuts into pieces.
Place in a buttered pan.
Mix the eggs with enough milk to saturate the donuts.
Add raisins, cinnamon and sugar to suit your taste.
You can add chopped apples, if you prefer.
Pour the liquid mixture over the donuts; the liquid will saturate the donuts.
Set the pan inside another pan partially filled with water for a steam bath.
Bake at 350° until knife will come out clean.
This will probably take at least 1 hour or more for a large batch and 45 minutes for a family size serving.
Let the pudding cool before serving.

title: sicilian dinner
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add tomato paste, water and seasonings (garlic, basil and oregano if desired).
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Drain well.
Heat milk and cubed cream cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add 1/2 of Parmesan, 1/4 teaspoon garlic, green pepper and pinch of salt. Add noodles.
Put alternate layers of meat and noodle mixtures into greased casserole dish.
End with meat mixture.
Add rest of Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 9x13 in. pan.
Crumble one tube of crackers in margarine.
Mix soups, sour cream and chicken, and pour over crackers.
Top with the other tube of crackers.
Lay a few parts of margarine on top of crackers.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes.

title: rolison's banana pudding
directions: Beat cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Mix 3 cups milk and vanilla pudding mix.
Blend until thick.
Add cream cheese mixture and vanilla flavoring; mix.
Add Cool Whip and beat mixture until smooth.
Line dish with bananas and vanilla wafers. Pour mixture over wafers.
Layer with bananas.
Chill.

title: crab imperial(lo-cal)
directions: Combine the crab meat, pimiento and celery in a mixing bowl. Crumble the slices of bread and add to the mixture.
Gently add the egg whites, yogurt, Worcestershire, cayenne, mustard, salt substitute and lemon juice.
Place in a sprayed casserole dish. Top with a sprinkle of paprika.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, until lightly brown.
Calories:

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Bring 2/3 of the milk to a boil.
Mix the flour into a smooth paste with the remainder of the milk; mix in hot water.
Add sugar, butter and beaten egg yolks.
Bring to a boil; cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and pour in reserved pineapple juice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into florets.
Cook bacon and crumble into bacon bits; combine mayo, sugar and vinegar and mix with broccoli, cauliflower, bacon bits and onions.
Mix well.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Chill before serving.

title: marinated salad
directions: Marinate
all
ingredients
in	plastic
container with tight seal
(to
turn
over) at least overnight.	Turn over a time or two.
Serve in salad bowl lined with lettuce.
Dump in marinated veggies and add olives, cucumbers, cherry tomatoes, green pepper, etc.

title: braunschweiger spread
directions: Mix. Shape in bowl or a ball and chill.

title: applesauce
directions: Mix apple, water and sugar in a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Microwave on Full power 8 to 9 minutes.
Blend.
Add cinnamon.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown
meat
with
onion
and pepper.
Add regular size canned ingredients with juices and other ingredients.
Simmer up to one hour.
Serve with cornbread or tortilla chips.

title: sensational beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef across the grain into very thin strips. In large skillet over high heat, melt margarine and cook the beef and onion until beef is no longer pink and onion is tender.
Stir in soup and paprika.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to very low.
Stir in sour cream.
Gently heat through.
Serve over noodles.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend cake mix, oil, water and eggs.
Stir in chips (1 cup nuts if desired).
Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Top of cookies will look pale.

title: tijuana torte
directions: Brown the lean ground beef and onion.
Drain off any excess grease. Add taco seasoning, mixing well.
Add green chilies and stewed tomatoes.
Let simmer about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
(I use a 9 x 13-inch pan for this dish; that way you have 3 stacks of tortillas.)
Put one corn tortilla in pan. Add spoonful of meat mixture on top of tortilla. Sprinkle with cheese.
Keep layering tortillas with mixture and cheese until mixture is used up. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese has melted, about 20 minutes.
Wonderful potluck dish.

title: tomato broil
directions: Halve tomatoes.
Add salt, pepper, basil and butter.
Broil 4 minutes.
Take out and top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Broil until brown.

title: fudge dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, mix 1 cup brown sugar and cocoa. Stir in 2 cups water.
Add 12 marshmallows, quartered.
Spoon over this a box of devil's food cake mix, which has been made according to directions on box.
Top with 1 cup nut meats.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Use with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Beat eggs; add butter, then add sugar.
Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Before adding raisins, roll in flour. Have real stiff dough.
Bake at 325° until done.
Makes 3 layers. Top with Coconut Icing.

title: pie crust
directions: Cream 1/2 cup flour with shortening.
Add water.
Mix well. Add rest of flour.
Mix lightly.
Roll out pie crust.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and roll in pecans.
Chill.

title: raspberry brownies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with electric mixer until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs and chocolate.
Mix well.
Add flour and again, mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon half of batter into greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Spread jam over batter.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 28 to 30 minutes.

title: apple and cherry sponge cakes
directions: Beat the eggs, cream of tartar, sugar and vanilla together until thick.
Fold in the flour and the chopped apple.
Divide the mixture between approximately 15 double thicknesses paper cases and sprinkle the cherries over each.
Arrange, 5 at a time, in a circle in the microwave and cook for 45 seconds to 1 minute on High, until the cakes are just dry on top.
Do not overcook.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Put all ingredients through grinder and mix together. Spread on buns and wrap in foil and freeze. Remove from freezer, thaw partially, bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: louisiana red beans and rice
directions: Drain beans.
In a
6-quart
heavy pot, add beans and 3 quarts of fresh water.
Cover
and
simmer
1 hour.
Check and make sure water doesn't boil down too far;
keep beans covered with water at all
times.
Add rest of the ingredients, except cooked rice, to the
beans.
If needed, add more water to keep beans covered with water.
Simmer, partially covered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or
until liquid
has
thickened.
Remove the bay leaves and discard.
Serve over
the
cooked rice and all you need is a pan of cornbread and some hungry people.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt into an ungreased square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch), mix until blended (in pan) with a fork.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly (1 to 2 minutes).
Bake for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan until ready to be frosted with your favorite frosting or the following glaze.

title: honey cinnamon swirl
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt in heavy saucepan.
Heat until shortening melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Add eggs and milk to yeast.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
On a floured surface, knead dough until elastic.
In a well-greased bowl turn dough so top is greased.
Cover.
Let rise in warm, draft free place 1 hour or until double.
Punch down.
Let rest 10 minutes. Divide dough in half.
Roll in rectangle, 12 x 16-inches.
Brush with butter.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all except potato chips.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and top with potato chip crumbs.
Bake at 400° until hot and bubbly.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Pour sauce in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 baking dish. Place breasts over sauce. In bowl, mix cheese, oil and bread crumbs; sprinkle over chicken. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cover pan after 20 to 25 minutes so that cheese does not burn.

title: horseradish spread
directions: Sprinkle unflavored gelatin over 1/4 cup cold water; let stand 1 minute.
Dissolve lemon-flavored gelatin in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add unflavored gelatin mixture, stirring until dissolved. Add sour cream, horseradish and mayonnaise, stirring until blended.
Pour mixture into lightly oiled 4-cup mold.
Cover and chill until firm.
Unmold on purple kale.
Spread with beef on ham biscuits.

title: mandarin orange and pineapple salad(15 servings)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle jello over mixture. Stir well.
Spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Combine pecans and coconut.
Sprinkle on top.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.

title: ambrosia punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except club soda and ice.
Mix well. Add club soda and ice just before serving.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: marinade for steaks
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate with steaks.
Drain and grill steaks.
Delicious.

title: easy cookies
directions: Blend cake mix and Crisco well with pastry blender or hands. Add milk.
Refrigerate 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook
carrots,	drain
and cool.
Cut onion and pepper. Set aside.
With
mixer,
mix remaining ingredients together. Layer in casserole	dish the carrots, onion and pepper.
Pour tomato mixture
over
layered
carrots and let set at least 12 hours before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise and soups until smooth.
Add chicken, celery and water chestnuts.
Pour in lightly greased casserole dish. Cover with stuffing mix.
Melt margarine and drizzle over the top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: dill burger
directions: Pickles can be big, little or halved. Wrap pickle with ground beef; totally enclosing pickle. Wrap with sliced bacon. Brown in a skillet or cook over open flame in pit. Serve with salad and beans.

title: venison easy sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in margarine in heavy skillet, mix Sloppy Joe seasoning mix with tomato paste and water.
Add venison in skillet along with celery, bell pepper and onions.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve on hamburger bun or open face or closed.

title: cream drop fudge
directions: Melt cream drops and peanut butter and oleo in microwave; add rest of ingredients and mix well.
May pour in greased pan and later cut in squares or drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: swiss cheese onion pie
directions: Cut cheese into thin slices.
Saute onion in butter and place in bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle cheese with flour and place on top of onion.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper.
Pour on top of cheese and onion.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, then at 300° for 25 minutes.
Crumble crisp bacon on top and serve.
Serves 6.

title: super easy sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Cover and bake in moderate oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of oleo.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Mix together.
Press in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes (cool).

title: layer cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Mix and add sifted flour, baking powder and salt, alternately with milk, to first mixture.
Add vanilla and beat.
Bake in 2 greased pans at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: refrigerator fruit salad
directions: Combine the beaten egg yolks, milk and sugar in top of a double boiler and cook over hot water to form a thin custard, coating spoon.
Cool.
Combine cherries with drained pineapple and cut up pears.
Add marshmallows and lemon juice.
Stir into these ingredients the custard and fold in the stiffly beaten whipping cream.
Pour salad mixture into a large pan and let stand 24 hours in the refrigerator, but not in the freezing unit.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, cream of tartar, cold water and dash of salt in top of double boiler.
Beat 1 minute.
Cook over boiling water, beating constantly, until mixture forms peaks, about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat until frosting is of spreading consistency.
Makes enough to cover tops and sides of two 3-inch layers or tops and sides of two 9-inch layers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs, then add oil, sugar, grated zucchini and vanilla.
Cream all these together.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans (2 1/2 x 4 x 8-inch).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bean chalupa
directions: Place beans (which have been soaked in 4 cups water).
Roast pork and rest of ingredients in rest of water in heavy kettle. Cover and simmer about 5 hours or until roast falls apart.
Break up roast.
Uncover and cook until thick, about 1/2 hour.
Serve over corn chips.
Pass condiments:
chopped tomatoes, diced avocado, chopped onion, shredded lettuce, grated cheese (Cheddar) and taco sauce or hot sauce.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados with a fork. Stir in onion, lemon juice, salt and chili powder.
Put in serving bowl. Spread mayonnaise over mixture, sealing to edges of bowl. Chill.

title: easy brownies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Put in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Add the flour and lemon extract.
Spread dough on large greased cookie sheet.
Add 1 tablespoon cherry pie filling at regular intervals, using 1 can of filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, vinegar and oil.
Let cool.
Drain beans, corn and peas and combine in a bowl.
Chop fine the pepper, onion and celery and add to beans, corn and peas.
Marinate overnight with vinegar dressing.

title: old fashioned caramel icing
directions: While 1 cup sugar is caramelizing over medium low heat, simmer remaining sugar and milk.
Bring sugar/milk combination to a boil, then add butter.
Once sugar has caramelized, combine with other ingredients, while still cooking using electric beater.
Beat while on medium low heat until it begins to boil again and forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat, but continue to beat until creamy.

title: citrus fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serves 30.

title: rich chocolate pudding
directions: Coarsely chop the chocolate; set aside.
Stir sugar and cornstarch together in small saucepan until thoroughly blended. Gradually stir in milk until blended.
Add chopped chocolate. Cook, stirring, over medium heat until chocolate is melted and mixture begins to boil.
Cook, stirring, until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Pour into 4 custard cups. Cool at room temperature before serving.
Add garnishes, if desired.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl. Separately cook until dry 2 packages chopped broccoli (use little water). Add to other ingredients and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle top with crumbled Cheddar cheese crackers. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Place all except cheese in blender.
Pour in greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange and onion salad
directions: Tear clean lettuce into pieces.
Arrange on salad plate. Place oranges, onions and olives on lettuce.
Salt and pepper. Mix herbs with olive oil and vinegar.
Drizzle over salad.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread mixture on tortillas, roll up and chill, in icebox, overnight, before slicing.

title: apple dip
directions: Soften the cream cheese and mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Add chopped peanuts.
Dip sliced raw apples in mixture.

title: coffee and spice pecans
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add pecans and bring to a boil.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Spoon onto wax paper, separating pecans with a fork.
Store in an airtight container.
Yields 3 cups.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs well. Sift together flour, soda, and salt and add to mixture with 2 cups of cocktail juice. Then fold in fruit. Bake in oblong pan at 300 for 45 - 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Beat eggs, then add 1 cup brown sugar, shortening, salt and vanilla. Beat until it is fluffy. Add peanut butter and the rest of the ingredients.
Put into muffin tins or one loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix together and freeze all or part of mixture.
Pour 3 quarts of ginger ale over mixture in a punch bowl.

title: carrot celebration cake
directions: In a bowl mix sugar, brown sugar, flours, baking soda, baking powder, salt or substitute, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg, cloves and reserve.
In a blender/food processor mince raisins then add to processor the canola oil, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Blend at pulse to smooth.
Combine that mix to grated carrots, pineapple and nut pieces.
Mix until blended.
Divide into 3 greased and floured 8 inch or 9 inch round pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 70 minutes until knife inserted in middle comes out without any moisture.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Unroll crescent rolls.
Pinch the triangles together so the dough will make a solid rectangle.
Soften cream cheese and spread on dough.
Brown sausage and drain.
Put sausage on top of cream cheese.
Roll up like a jelly roll and refrigerate or freeze until you are ready to cook them.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Put the first 8 ingredients in a large pan on top of the stove and cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Cool until the pan is cool enough to touch.
Add flour and soda to the cooled mixture and stir well until no more flour is showing.
Put into greased and floured 10 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° until done (starts to come away from the edges, touch test springs back or toothpick comes clean).
You be the judge, not good if undercooked.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Then mix together 2 beaten eggs and cream cheese along with confectioners sugar.
Pour over first layer and bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: beef rice fiesta
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, brown ground beef and drain.
Add the butter or margarine with the rice mixture and onion to the beef. Slowly add the hot water, green pepper, tomatoes and chili powder. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover saucepan and simmer until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender, approximately 15 minutes. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Allow to melt.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple squares
directions: Combine flour, salt and 1/3 cup sugar.
Cut in butter; press into a well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange apples on top of this; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine 1/3 cup sugar with cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 358° for 20 minutes.

title: daddy's makin' supper
directions: Bring frying pan with oil to medium heat.
Crack and add egg to pan, with shell, break yolk.
Turn gently when egg slides intact onto spatula.
Drain on paper towel, but do not dry oil from egg. Spread each slice of bread with one teaspoon mayonnaise.
Add egg to bread.
Add tomato, if in season; if not, 1 thick slice of onion.
Salt and pepper to taste, and enjoy.

title: banana milkshake
directions: Put 6 to 8 ice cubes in blender and milk to cover the ice cubes, vanilla, Sweet 'N Low or sugar.
Blend this until cubes dissolve.
Add two sliced, ripe bananas and blend.
This may not be as thick as a milkshake from McDonald's, but it's a delicious beverage.
Strawberries can also be used.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and blend cocoa. Stir sugar and eggs. Mix well with remaining ingredients, except marshmallows. Pour into well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle top with marshmallows.

title: chicken bog
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Melt oleo and saute onion, celery and pepper.
Add broth and heat to boiling; add rice.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook until rice is tender.

title: chocolate chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Bake for 65 to 70 minutes.
Combine boiling water and cocoa.
Cool.
Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt into mixing bowl.
Make a well; add in order the oil, egg yolks, cocoa mixture and vanilla.
Beat with a spoon until smooth.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar to very stiff peaks, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not underbeat.
Pour egg yolk mixture over egg whites.
Fold in with a rubber spatula until blended.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Cool upside down in pan on a funnel for 4 hours.

title: grandmother's tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients. Work into soft dough that will roll out well.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Combine flour, meal, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add eggs and milk.
Stir just to moisten.
Add cracklings.
Bake in hot, well-greased pan at 450° until golden brown.

title: egg and sausage strata
directions: Grease or lightly spray 13 x 9-inch pan. Place bread cubes in pan. In a large bowl, mix together eggs, milk, salt, pepper and dry mustard. Pour over bread cubes. Top with cheese, then sausage. Refrigerate overnight (or at least 8 hours). Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: hamburger tortilla casserole
directions: First saute onions in skillet, then brown hamburger meat. Next, mix cream of cheese and cream of mushroom soup, enchilada sauce and jalapeno peppers.
Place a layer of tortilla chips in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix hamburger meat and soup mixture. Then pour that over tortilla chips.
Sprinkle some shredded cheese over casserole.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apples into buttered baking dish and cover with sugar and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Prepare pudding as directed; set aside to set.
Soften cream cheese.
Mix with pudding.
(Mixture will be lumpy.) Set aside. Boil water; add butter and bring to boil (simmer).
Add flour; mix well.
Take off heat.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat each well. Pour mixture into greased 10 x 15 1/2-inch jelly roll pan (don't flour).
Bake for 20 minutes at 425° or until golden brown. Mixture will puff up.
Let cool; mash with hand.
Spread pudding mixture on top.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Drizzle chocolate syrup; chill until set.

title: strawberry sherbet
directions: Combine strawberries and sugar; beat well with electric mixer. Stir in buttermilk.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Freeze mixture until slushy, then beat well with mixer.
Freeze until firm.
This is delicious on a cream cheese pound cake.

title: no crust egg custard
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a greased and floured pan. Mixture can also be put into a pie crust and baked for a regular pie.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Heat Jell-O, gelatin, pineapple and baby food to dissolve, then cool to touch.
Fold in buttermilk and Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Melt oleo in skillet.
Saute onion and bell pepper 1 or 2 minutes.
Mix other ingredients except green onion tops.
Pour into a large casserole dish.
Cover and cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover, stir in green onion tops and a little water if needed and cook for 30 minutes more.

title: neiman-marcus dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: nina's casserole
directions: Brown beef with salt, sugar, garlic and tomato sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes; add onions.
Simmer 5 more minutes.
Boil noodles (per package directions).
Mix the cream cheese and sour cream.
Stack in layers like lasagna; top with Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese, grated.
Put in oven at 350° to melt the cheese for 40 minutes.

title: cheese cake (regular or sugar-free)
directions: Melt butter and stir in vanilla wafers and sugar; mix until blended well.
Press into a large cake dish or baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool and add the cheese cake mixture.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil all ingredients, except corn and soda for 5 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Remove and add soda; stir quickly.
Pour over popped corn.
Put in 2 large pans and bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring 2 to 3 times.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crumble cookies; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Press into square Pyrex baking dish.
Let set overnight before cutting.

title: george's lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Stir in tomato sauce special and water.
Sprinkle with basil and salt to taste.
Heat to boiling.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into cool pie shells. Makes 2 pies.

title: banana pie
directions: Slice bananas in bottom of crust.
Soften cream cheese with 1/2 cup milk.
Mix remaining milk with pudding mix and add to cream cheese mixture.
Pour into crust and top with coconut. Chill.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Grease pan and	pour
in cherry filling.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Melt	butter	and
pour
over top.
Sprinkle with nuts and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo and shortening; add both sugars, eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, baking soda and powder; then add to mixture.
Add last 5 ingredients while mixing with a spoon.
Use 1/4 cup per cookie (6 cookies per sheet).
Cook 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 30 to 40 cookies.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Bake the sweet potatoes, then mash them with oleo, add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 2 deep pie shells and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cut all vegetables into small pieces, including water chestnuts and onions.
Add all ingredients except butter and crackers.
Mix well and pour in greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Crush crackers and mix in melted butter.
Pour over vegetables and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain part of juice from potatoes. Warm potatoes and 3/4 stick margarine, then mash well. Add a little juice to make creamy. Beat eggs, sugar, milk and nutmeg. Mix potato mixture. Cook for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: mine momma's green chili
directions: Fry cubed pork steak until browned and almost cooked.
Stir in tomatoes, seasonings and chilies.
Add water (1, 2 or more cups) to make the green chili a saucelike consistency.
Cook until meat is done and tender.
Serve with cooked pinto beans, fried bread or tortillas.
Great.

title: bean soup
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bell pepper together; drain.
Add all other ingredients and simmer until thoroughly heated.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in oleo. Add soups and rice. Place in deep casserole dish with chicken on top. Bake 2 1/2 hours at 275°. Turn chicken once so it will brown on both sides.

title: hot crabmeat spread
directions: Mix all ingredients but crab meat and almonds.
When well blended, mix in crab meat.
Put into an ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle almonds on the top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Shred lettuce.
Drain beans. Combine lettuce, beans, meat and cheese.
Cut onions, as many as preferred.
Add and mix.
Just before serving, add chips and then add dressing to suit taste.

title: georgia peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Shell:
Crush Oreo cookies very finely or grind in food processor.
Add melted butter.
Press into bottom and sides of pie plate.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix
macaroni
and
cheese
according to package directions. Mix macaroni and
cheese,
tuna, soup and peas.
Place in casserole dish;
cover with seasoned bread crumbs.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy. Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender for 1 to 3 minutes. Pour into a 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes its own crust and is very, very good.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add milk and well beaten egg.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut tops of baked potatoes (lengthwise) and scoop out potatoes.
Mash potatoes with 1 cup sour cream, onion, salt and dried chives.
Fill skins with potato mixture and bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Add water and pineapple juice to make 2 cups.
Boil.
Dissolve Jell-O.
Allow Jell-O to jell slightly.
Add mixture of cheese, pineapple and Cool Whip.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken soup, celery soup, Veg-All, cheese and milk in boiler.
Heat until cheese melts.
Add chicken and mix well.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Top with biscuits.
I roll biscuits out and put on top of chicken mixture.
Bake in 400° oven until biscuits are browned, about 12 minutes.

title: blueberry jello
directions: Make jello and let cool.
Add 1 can blueberry pie filling. Chill until set and frost with Cool Whip topping.

title: bootsie porter's cinnamon apple cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Mix well after each addition.
Fold in apples.
Pour into greased and floured pan (or use Baker's Joy).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mom's prune cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix. Add remaining ingredients; blend thoroughly.
Bake in tube pan for 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: smothered steak roll-ups
directions: Pound steak with meat hammer.
Place 1/3 cup stuffing near center of each steak slice, roll and fasten with skewers.
Brown in butter.
Add soup and water.
Cover; cook over low heat 1 hour or until tender.
Spoon sauce over meat during cooking.

title: german farmers breakfast
directions: In large
skillet, saute bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain. Crumble.
Drain
off
all but 3 tablespoons drippings. Add green pepper,
onion,
potatoes,	salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, over medium heat until golden.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture and stir until
melted.
Pour
eggs and cook over low heat until set. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: campfire stew
directions: Brown hamburger, green pepper and onion.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Add together and add other ingredients; serve.

title: tuna pasta casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: marinated salad
directions: Slice cabbage, onion and green bell peppers.
Add vinegar and sugar and toss; salt and pepper.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour, then serve.

title: st. patrick's green velvet cake(gladys starr's)
directions: Beat eggs in mixer.
Add sugar, oil and vinegar, then blend well.
Sift flour and soda together and add to egg mixture alternately with flour.
Blend ingredients well, then add vanilla and cake coloring.

title: quick blackberry cobbler
directions: Put berries in 9-inch square pan. Sprinkle jello and cake mix over berries. Pour water over this. Sprinkle on pecans and cinnamon. Drizzle on butter. Bake at 350 degrees until top is brown and fruit is bubbly, about 40 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken breasts
directions: Clean and skin chicken pieces.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Salt and pepper.
Mix the 2 half bottles of barbecue sauce together.
Pour over the chicken. Cover with aluminum foil tightly and bake at 350° for
1 hour.
Chicken will fall off the bone!

title: european almond cake
directions: Beat yolks with sugar until creamy and thick.
Add almonds; add flour and baking powder.
Mix and stir.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold until creamed mixture.
Line with wax paper three 9-inch layer pans and bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Step 1:
Grease large cookie sheet.
Bring to a boil in saucepan 2 sticks butter, water
and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Remove from heat and add 2 cups flour, sugar and salt.

title: pig licking cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350°. Makes 3 layers. Cool.

title: party biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased mini muffin cups. Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: jerry lewis' vinegar cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and blend well.
Add chocolate and add flour and salt to creamed mixture, alternating with sour milk.
Mix soda and vinegar and blend into cake mixture. Pour into greased layer pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 3 cheese pig slop(leftover dish)
directions: In a medium size baking dish, cover bottom with 1/3 potatoes. Then 1/3 roast beef, then cover with 1/3 gravy.
Add cheese of your choice.
Repeat until gone.
Place in preheated oven at 350° to 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve over toast.

title: dottie's company string beans
directions: Heat
beans
in
boiling
water
and drain.
Add one can cream of
mushroom
soup,
heat again in serving dish in oven. Just before
ready
to serve, top with one can of onion rings. Mix some in string beans, but put most on the top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done, about 30 minutes.
Remove from water. Let cool to touch.
Remove meat; separate into bite sized pieces. Simmer butter and onion together.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and milk together in a bowl.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar, vanilla, and butter.
Stir in milk.
Beat about 15 minutes.
Spread coconut in bottoms of pie shells.
Pour in liquid mixture. Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cool banana pudding
directions: Combine milk and water together with a wire whisk.
Add pudding and blend until smooth.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Whip the whipping cream.
Fold in pudding mixture.
Layer pudding, wafers and bananas.
Top with maraschino cherries (optional).

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Form into 2 loaves.
Put into baking pan.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serve with oven fried potatoes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower if too big.
In a large pan, combine water, broccoli, cauliflower, onions and celery.
Cover and boil for 30 minutes.
Add canned soup and cheese.
Simmer over low heat until cheese melts.
Add milk and heat through. Recipe is easy to cut in half.

title: crabmeat pizza
directions: Spread cream cheese (mix onion and garlic powder into cream cheese) on small silver tray or plate.
Spread chili sauce on top of cream cheese mixture.
Drain crabmeat and spread on top of chili sauce.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with crackers (Wheat Thins).

title: potato casserole
directions: Buy freshest and youngest greens you can find and wash and look thoroughly.
May take 3 to 6 times washing, depending on how dirty they were.
Wash until there is no grit in bottom of sink or pan washed in.
Cut the largest part of stem out; these may be very tough and stringy if not young greens.

title: no cook cherry pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. Beat until fluffy.
Gradually add sweetened condensed milk. (Condensed milk must be used.)
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Turn into prepared crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours in refrigerator.
Do not freeze.
Put cherry pie filling on top.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: creamy pimento cheese
directions: Combine cheeses and mix well with mixer.
Add mayonnaise and garlic powder.
Mix and stir in pimento.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook the sugar, water and peanuts until golden brown.
Add the vanilla and baking soda.
Pour into pan and cool.

title: debbie's zucchini cakes
directions: Cut squash open.
Scoop out seeds.
Place squash skin-side down in pan with one inch of water.
Add 1/2 to 1 tablespoon of butter in each half.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 50 minutes or until soft at 350°.
To serve, add warm maple syrup to taste.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potato,
brown
sugar, butter, egg yolks, spices and salt in a large
mixing bowl.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add evaporated milk,
mix
until just combined.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually
add
sugar, beating stiff. Fold into potato mixture.
Pour
into
pastry
shell.
Bake at 400° for ten minutes, reduce heat
to 350° and bake 45 minutes or until set. Cool.
Top with whipped topping if desired.

title: canned corned beef hash
directions: Mix tomato sauce, onion, salt and mustard together.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Cover with a layer of corned beef hash, then sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat layers again and bake.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and pour into slightly greased, hot iron skillet.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Let stand 1 hour before serving.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and salt; let stand 10 to 13 minutes. Dissolve the soda in 1 or 2 teaspoons water.
Add soda, egg, oil and nuts to apples.
Sift flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to apples.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Dust each egg with a little flour.
Divide the sausage meat into 5 pieces.
On a floured surface, work each piece into an oval.
Place an egg into the center of each one; mold the sausage meat around it, making sure the surface is free from cracks.
Put the beaten egg and breadcrumbs onto separate plates; coat each egg first in the liquid egg, then in the breadcrumbs so that the surface is completely covered.
Coat each egg again if you like to ensure a really good surface.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello in water.
Add marshmallows and cream cheese and stir.
Chill to consistency of egg whites.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into oblong pan and refrigerate.
Later, stir to prevent ingredients from sinking to the bottom.

title: hot virginia dip
directions: Saute pecans in butter. Reserve.
Mix other ingredients together with a wooden spoon.
Put in deep-dish pie plate and top with pecans.
Chill until just before serving time.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with Wheat Thins, Triscuits or bread sticks.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Combine and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be cooked in microwave 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese drop biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients for dough and mix.
Combine buttermilk with slightly beaten egg white and mix. Add buttermilk and egg mixture to flour and stir.
Add cheese and mix well.

Drop by large spoonful onto baking sheet sprayed with non-stick cooking spray and bake at 400° for about 15 minutes. If the top of the biscuits do not brown, place under broiler for a few seconds to brown the tops.
Yield: 8-10 servings depending on the size of each biscuit.

title: carrots
directions: Place carrots in buttered or Pammed 1 1/2-quart casserole. Stir in croutons and cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Place over carrots.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 400°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix pumpkin as directed on can.
Pour into greased 12 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle cake mix over pumpkin.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gram's spaghetti sauce
directions: Cut up bacon and onion in small pieces and fry.
Add can of tomatoes.
Break into pieces.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Add cheese, cut into small pieces.
Put in when you turn fire out under skillet.
Cover with lid so cheese will melt.
Pour over drained spaghetti.

title: holy salmon croquettes
directions: Mix all together and make into croquettes or patties.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° of fry.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer 15 to 30 minutes.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Line the sides and bottom of large spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Mix cheesecake mixes according to box directions. Add softened cream cheese to preceding.
Fold in topping.

title: beef vegetable gumbo
directions: Simmer beef until tender.
Add other ingredients and cook for 1 hour.

title: peppers, tomatoes and onions(peperonata)
directions: Clean and slice peppers and onions.
Heat oil in frying pan. Add peppers and
onions;
cook
until
just tender.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Cover and
cook over low heat for 6 to 8 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 servings.
This is wonderful on an antipasto platter or on top of a sandwich.

title: little cherry cheesecakes
directions: Blend cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Put vanilla wafer in bottom of cupcake paper.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 370°.
Top with fruit filling.
Makes 17.

title: beef enchilada
directions: Brown beef in oil in skillet.
Add onion and saute with beef until tender.
Add garlic; saute 15 seconds.
Add chilies, chili powder, oregano, tomatoes with juice, salt and water.
Break up tomatoes and bring mixture to a boil.
Add rice.
Stir, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle dish with chopped parsley.
Place cheese on top.
Replace cover.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes until cheese has melted.
Serve.
Makes 4 servings, containing less than 350 calories each.

title: tortilla wraps
directions: Mix cream cheese, green chiles and olives together with fork. Spread approximately 2 to 3 tablespoons of cream cheese mixture evenly over a tortilla.
Roll tortilla up (use a toothpick, if needed to keep rolled) and put into the refrigerator for 1/2 hour or so.
Slice into 1/2 to 1-inch segments.
Place on plate and serve with salsa.

title: old fashioned bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Add rest of ingredients, except flour.
Add 4 cups flour; mix well.
Let set 1/2 hour in warm place.
Add rest of flour.
Knead well and let rise until double in bulk.
Make loaves and rolls.
Put in greased pans.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until brown for bread.
Bake rolls 40 minutes or until brown.

title: banana snack cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8 or 9-inch square pan.

title: mrs. abe lincoln's mystery pudding
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together; then stir in next 4 ingredients.
Spread resulting batter in an 8-inch square buttered tin.
Mix brown sugar and cocoa; spread over batter in pan.
Over all, pour 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cake that doesn't last
directions: Melt together over medium heat and pour over cold cake.

title: healthy oatmeal cake
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, oats and raisins (or dates or blueberries). In a medium bowl, stir together the eggs, yogurt, canola oil, applesauce, honey and vanilla. Pour wet ingredients into the dry and stir well. Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven about 30 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: parmesan onion canapes
directions: Mix mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, chopped onion and milk. Spread on toasted cocktail bread; place on baking sheets.
Broil 4 inches from source of heat for 2 to 3 minutes, or until golden and bubbly.
Add garnishes, if desired.
Makes 36.

title: zucchini (kirbi szuspeibe)
directions: Take the meat of the zucchini, grate it, salt the grated zucchini and set aside.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix together and microwave until melted.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: spicy chili sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to boiling; simmer until thick as wanted, about 1 to 2 hours.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Pour, boiling hot, into hot jars.
Adjust caps. Process 15 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yields about 8 pints.

title: oliebollen(fried cakes)
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add egg, potato water and yeast. Mix well and add currants, citron, raisins and flour sifted with salt.
Let rise until light.
Drop from spoon in hot fat (365°). Drain on absorbent paper and roll in sugar.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken with 1/2 onion, salt and pepper and bouillon cubes until done.
Remove meat from bone and save 3 cups broth.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Drain broth.
Add onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Add corn, butter beans, tomatoes, ketchup and vinegar; cook for 2 hours.
The last 30 minutes, add cut up chicken and potatoes, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, marjoram, bay leaf, butter and sugar.
Add water, if necessary, to make more soupy.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: no bake fruit cake roll
directions: Pour the milk over marshmallows and let stand.
Mix other ingredients and add to marshmallows.
Mix well.
Place some crumbs on a square of wax paper and form a roll about 2-inches in diameter and place in crumbs.
Roll up in crumbs and wax paper. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice and serve.
Makes 4 large rolls.

title: hashed onions(vintage recipe)
directions: Put the onions, milk and water in a saucepan.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Drain the onions and cut them up.
Put the onions back into the pan.
Add the butter, salt, pepper, nutmeg and light cream.
Cook, uncovered, stirring once in a while. Serve piping hot.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb
in small pieces.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add 1 cup sugar
and rhubarb. Cook until tender; add egg yolks mixed with 1/4
cup
of
sugar
and flour.
Stir until mixture thickens. Pour in
baked
9-inch
pie
shell and top with meringue.

title: turn over spinach pie
directions: Mix well first four ingredients, let set overnight.
Drain spinach, heat garlic in oil until brown.
Put spinach and 4 slices of cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook.
Roll out dough, cut in squares, 4 x 4-inches.
Fill each square with 2 teaspoon spinach filling.
Fold.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: kissing cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and mix into butter mixture. Shape into small balls.
Roll in granulated sugar and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a chocolate kiss in the center of each one.
Return to oven for 2 to 5 minutes, until golden brown.

title: golden corn squares
directions: In bowl, combine slightly beaten eggs, cream-style corn, milk, instant minced onion and pepper; stir in cooked rice, cubed luncheon meat and cubed cheese.
Turn in ungreased 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until knife inserted just off center comes off clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Cut in squares.
Makes 6 servings.

title: butterflied party franks
directions: Cut each frankfurter crosswise into 4 sections.
Cut each section in half lengthwise to make 8 pieces.
Split ends of each piece within 1/2-inch of the center.
Set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Take chicken off the bones.
In your broth, cook noodles.
Put back your chicken.
Add soup and cheese; heat until cheese melts.
Put chicken and mixture in a baking pan.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Heat at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Cut
shortening
into
flour;
add rest of ingredients. Stir just
long enough to mix.
Put in greased 9-inch round or square pan.
Top
with
small
pieces of butter.
Bake at 450° for 12
to 15 minutes.
Serve warm in bowl topped with strawberries and milk.

title: chicken-dried beef
directions: Fry bacon and onion. Combine sour cream and mushroom soup. Cover baking dish with dried beef.
Place chicken breasts on top. Cover with soup, bacon, onion and dashes of lemon pepper. Bake at 350° in covered baking dish for 1 hour.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk well.
Mix fruit and melted butter. Heat until hot.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over fruit mixture.
Stir this around in the fruit.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over batter.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Turn down to 325° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: luscious apricot bars
directions: Rinse apricots.
Cover with water and boil 10 minutes.
Drain and cool; chop.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Mix butter, granulated sugar and 1 cup flour until crumbly.
Pack into pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Sift 1/3 cup flour, baking powder and salt.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and place in large heavy pan.
Add onion, celery and bacon or ham. Add just enough water to cover. Salt to taste. Boil until tender. Do not drain.
Beat egg.
Add flour and salt.
Blend well.
