Add to potato mixture. Stir and cook 5 minutes. Stir to keep from sticking. Add about 1 1/2 quarts milk depending on desired thickness.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Dip crackers, vegetables, pretzels, etc.

title: almond roca
directions: Spread almonds on cookie sheet or flat pan.
Melt butter, add sugar in heavy pan.
Cook rapidly, stirring constantly to prevent scorching; cook until dark brown.
Add vanilla.
Pour mixture over almonds.
Sprinkle Hershey bar pieces over top.
Let candy melt and then spread evenly.
Sprinkle more chopped almonds on top. When cool, break into pieces.

title: veggie soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add all ingredients together and cook until done (about 30 to 40 minutes).
Serve with hot cornbread.

title: macadamia nut cookies
directions: Beat the shortening and margarine or butter with electric mixer on medium-high for 30 minutes.
Add about half of the flour, brown sugar, sugar, eggs, vanilla and baking soda.
Beat in remaining flour.
Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: lime cucumber cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in boiling water.
Stir well and set aside to cool.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into large jello mold.
Place in refrigerator until well set.
Will serve 12 persons.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain water from broccoli.
Cut broccoli in small pieces, including ends, if not woody.
Add sunflower seeds, raisins, bacon and onion.
Toss this together.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over salad mixture, stirring well.
Let stand several hours before serving.

title: ginger lime pork
directions: Cut pork diagonally into 1/4-inch thick pieces.
Cut each slice into thin strips.
Set aside.
Slice asparagus diagonally into 1-inch long pieces.
Cut carrots into 2-inch long julienne pieces.
Heat one tablespoon oil over medium-high heat in a large skillet,
Add carrots; cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add asparagus; cook 1 minute more.
Lower heat to medium low.
Add 1 tablespoon wine.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender-crisp (4 to 5 minutes).
Remove.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: Combine meat, salt, 1/4 cup ketchup and onions; shape into 6 patties.
Fry or broil until done (about 5 minutes each side). Spread 1 tablespoon pizza flavored ketchup on each bun, then top with patty and a slice of cheese.
Place under broiler just long enough to melt cheese slightly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: high humidity buttercream frosting
directions: Blend Crisco, Dream Whip and vanilla.
Mix 4 to 6 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Add half the sugar, all of the flour and all of the milk.
Cut in with knife.
Add remaining sugar and beat until fluffy, about 6 minutes.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 11 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: original green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 can of onions into 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put the rest of the onions on top and bake for 5 more minutes or until onions are brown.

title: bubble bread
directions: Melt oleo.
Roll biscuits into ball.
Dip in oleo, then in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Layer alternately in a Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin chews
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine flour, soda, salt and oats. Set aside.
In large bowl, blend sugars at medium speed.
Add butter and mix.
Add honey, vanilla and eggs.
Mix until light and fluffy.
Add flour, raisins and nuts.
Blend until combined.
Do not overmix.
Drop by tablespoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 22 minutes or until golden brown.
Transfer to cool surface right away when done.

title: pasta house salad
directions: Wash and drain lettuce.
Break into small pieces.
Chill.
Add artichoke hearts, red onion and pimento . Mix olive oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and cheese.
Add to lettuce just before serving.
Toss until mixed completely.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken into eggs, then into bread crumbs, coating thoroughly.
In a medium skillet, heat olive oil. Cook chicken in oil until done and well browned on both sides. Pour spaghetti sauce into an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on sauce; top with Parmesan and Mozzarella cheeses.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until cheese is melted and lightly browned. Serves 4.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in a shallow pie plate.
Dredge chicken in mixture.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of flour.

title: walnut blue cheese chicken salad
directions: In large frypan place chicken, broth, onion and olive oil. Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Remove chicken from bones; cut into thin strips.
In large bowl mix parsley, rosemary, pepper, salt, lime juice, garlic, nuts and Blue cheese.
Let stand 15 minutes. Cook noodles; drain.
Add to chicken.
Arrange on lettuce cups; sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Arrange cherry tomatoes and celery around edge.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil, and eggs.
Add orange juice (or pineapple juice) and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Note:
I mix my apples, sugar and cinnamon when I start so the sugar and cinnamon get in the apples.
Pour batter alternately with the apples, ending with apples placed around the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: corn spoon
directions: Grease a 2 quart baking dish.
Beat the egg whites at room temperature till stiff but not dry and beat the yolks till thick and lemon colored.
Stir the cornmeal and salt into the scalded milk, beating hard.
Stir till consistency of thick mush.
Blend in the butter and corn and add baking powder.
Fold in the yolks, then whites.
Pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or till puffy and golden brown and a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Crush graham crackers into very small crumbs.
Cream sugar and margarine together.
Add eggs, milk and graham crackers alternately.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and spread filling between layers.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour pineapple into a casserole.
Mix sugar, flour and cheese together; sprinkle over the pineapple.
Mix butter and crackers together; crumble over mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°. Serves 10 to 12.

title: barbeque sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a large sauce pan.
Cook over low heat, slowly for about 2 hours.
Store in refrigerator.

title: heavenly cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage in squares.
Heat bacon grease on low heat.
Add onion.
Heat until translucent.
Add cabbage, mustard, onion and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Add water and grated carrot.
Cook in a large pot until cabbage is tender, approximately medium-high for 20 to 25 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: apple blackberry crisp
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, spread apples in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle sugar/flour mixture over apples.
Then spread blackberries over top.

title: scalloped eggs and bacon
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender, but not browned.
Stir flour into onion mixture.
Add milk all at once; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Continue cooking for 1 or 2 minutes longer.
Add cheeses and stir until melted.

title: cowboy cornbread
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch dish and place in the oven at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4. In a large bowl, mix the cornmeal, egg, milk, soda, salt, corn and oil, set aside.
Brown the beef in the microwave on high in a microwave safe colander set in a dish to catch the drippings for about 8-10 minutes.
Stir in the onions and the chilis.
Remove the dish from the oven, spread half the cornbread batter into the dish, cover with the beef mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Pour remaining batter over the cheese and return to the oven to bake for 40-50 minutes or until done.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Cover; let stand 20 minutes. Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add oat mixture. Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until smooth.
Add flour mixing well. Mix in oatmeal.
Refrigerate at least one hour or more.
Roll into balls size of walnut.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or lightly browned. Cool on racks.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: rice and pork chop casserole
directions: I use large iron frying pan greased with butter or margarine. Wash and drain rice.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle soup mix over rice. Place pork chops on top of this mixture.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over pork chops and add water.
Bake on 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Add water to beef consomme to make 2 cups.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter.
Cut round steak into strips (2 1/2 x 3/4-inch).
Add 4 tablespoons flour to sour cream.
Cook in crock-pot 3 to 4 hours on high or 8 to 12 hours on low.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.
Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs.
Add soda to boiling water. Mix into creamed mixture.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with orange juice and add nuts and mashed bananas. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: betty moore's chicken delight(english teacher at ghs)
directions: Grease large baking dish.
Layer in order (chicken, cheese, soup and stuffing).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat oil, sugar, orange juice and egg together.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together and place in a large mixing bowl with wheat germ, lemon rind and blueberries.
Combine with liquid mixture and blend.
Bake in muffin tins for 20 to 25 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: butterscotch peanut bars
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add brown sugar and peanut butter.
Mix well and bring to just boiling over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and let cool until lukewarm.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt and set aside.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: stroganoff
directions: Cube meat.
Brown in Dutch oven.
Add balance of ingredients. Bake at 250° for 4 to 4 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: 5 minute chicken
directions: Put thighs close together in baking dish.
Cover with onion. Liberally drizzle with soy sauce.
Bake until tender, 45 minutes, at 350°.

title: fresh rhubarb pie
directions: Prepare pastry for 10-inch 2-crust pie.
Heat oven to 425°. Stir together sugar and flour.
Turn half the rhubarb and oranges/strawberries into pastry-lined pie dish.
Sprinkle with half the sugar mixture.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top pastry.
Seal and flute.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: green beans almond
directions: Cook almonds in butter over low heat until golden, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add salt and lemon juice.
Pour over hot, drained beans.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Beat together the milk, pudding and ice cream and pour into crust.

title: jalapeno black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in a small amount of oil.
Add ground meat and brown.
Fold in Ro-Tel and black-eyed peas.
Place in oblong baking dish.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Cook and mash broccoli, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Saute onions in oil.
Add 4 tablespoons butter, then remaining ingredients, except crumbs.
Place in greased casserole and top with crumbs and 2 tablespoons of butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: relish
directions: Grind sweet peppers, tomatoes, cabbage and onions.
Squeeze free of water.
Mix sugar and vinegar in large pan.
Add salt and spice bag.
Bring to a boil and add ground mixture; grind hot pepper and add.
Cook until well done.
Pack in hot jars and seal at once.
Yields 25 pints.

title: three bean bake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: peach pie filling fruit salad
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Refrigerate for several hours, if possible, before serving.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake 4 to 6 potatoes until done.
Carefully scoop potato out of skin and put it in a bowl.
Separate eggs; add yolks, butter, cream, salt and pepper.
Blend until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into potatoes.
Fill skins with mixture. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add the sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly, but well.
Combine the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon in a separate bowl.
Then add to zucchini mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) greased loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool on rack.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake shoulders 40 minutes per pound or until tender.
Remove all fat.
Shred or dice meat.
Add meat to remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, green pepper and garlic in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Add tomatoes, peas, corn and carrots. Simmer 1/2 to 1 hour and season to taste as you go.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Feeds 5 hungry people.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Toast pecans for 5 minutes in margarine in oven at 350°.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, brown sugar and 1 cup evaporated milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and chill (can be cooked the day before).

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix in onion, green pepper, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and ketchup.
Simmer until onion and green pepper are tender.
Cook macaroni according to directions. Mix macaroni and hamburger mixture in casserole and cover with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine pretzels, butter and sugar together. Bake in pan at 350° for 8 minutes. Let cool.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into chunks.
Cook in pineapple juice until tender.
Drain and reserve syrup.
Add remaining ingredients except marshmallows; mix well.
Put mixture into casserole. Lightly press marshmallows on top.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
In a 2-quart baking dish, place a layer of potatoes and slices of onion.
Sprinkle a small amount of salt and pepper on each layer, keep layering until your baking dish is about 1-inch from the top.
Pour soup on top and then the water.

title: light pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixer bowl. Beat on third speed for 20 minutes. Bake in ungreased tube pan.
Put in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Combine until onion and pepper are tender.

title: green salad with mad
directions: Mix together, then add dressing.
Italian is best for taste.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Saute onion and green pepper in oil. Add all ingredients and thoroughly blend.
Form into a ball.
(If too runny, set in refrigerator for an hour.) Garnish with 1/2 olives on the top.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

In a bowl, combine peaches, brown sugar, 2 tablespoons cornstarch and 1/2 teaspoon almond flavoring. In another bowl, place cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, 2 teaspoons cornstarch and 1/8 teaspoon almond flavoring.
Blend until creamy; stir in almonds.
Turn cream mixture into unbaked pie shell and spread evenly.
Cover with peaches.
Dot with butter and cover with top crust.
Flute edges and vent top.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 400° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: johnny appleseed cake
directions: Sift together
all dry ingredients.
Add dates, raisins and margarine to flour mixture.
Add applesauce with soda; mix well and
add
to flour mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or large tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Sprinkle vegetables with the salt, cover with ice and let set for 3 hours.
Mix the remaining ingredients and heat.
Add cucumbers and bring to a boil, but do not boil.
Turn a few times as they heat.
Place in jars and seal.

title: orange-kiwifruit salad
directions: Arrange orange and kiwifruit slices on salad greens.
Top with grapes. Serve with Honey-Spice Dressing.
Make 6 servings.
No fat or cholesterol.

title: egg nog
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat yolks and sugar together.
Add milk and brandy.
Blend well.
Beat heavy cream until slightly stiff.
Add cream and egg whites to brandy mixture.
Store in closed container.
Shake well before serving. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Yields 1/2 gallon.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: In bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt.
Add melted butter and beaten eggs and beat slightly with rotary beater.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla, blending with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oven baked potatoes
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the hash browns, soup, sour cream, cheese, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup melted butter. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine the remaining butter and corn flakes and put on top of potato mixture evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dirty rice(serves 12 people)
directions: Saute
gizzards,
livers, onions and paprika in the oil for a few minutes.
Add
onions,	parsley and bell peppers and cook 1/2 hour.
Add already cooked rice, stir good and bake at low temperature for approximately 1/2 hour.
Serves 12 people.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: In a 2 cup container, dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water and 1/2 teaspoon sugar; let stand 1 hour.
Cream shortening and 1/2 cup sugar.
Combine yeast and shortening mixture with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 1 hour.
Refrigerate until you are ready to bake.
Make dough into 1-inch round balls and place 3 balls into each greased muffin cup.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 1 1/2 to 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 28 rolls.

title: festive carrots and pineapple
directions: Combine pineapple juice, sugar, butter, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Cook and stir until clear and thickened.
Add pineapple and carrots.
Heat and serve immediately.
If desired, garnish with lime peel.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: You will need 1 pizza pan.

title: white cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs, well beaten, soda mixed with sour milk, salt, extracts and about 5 cups flour. Roll thin and cut with cookie cutters.
Grease pan and bake in moderate oven about 12 minutes.
Makes 90 cookies.
Ice with confectioners sugar icing.
These are easier to cut if chilled before cutting.

title: carrot casserole
directions: In medium saucepan, steam carrots until tender; drain and set aside.
In a medium saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter and saute onion until clear.
Combine flour, milk and spices.
Add to onion and heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
In a small skillet, melt 3 tablespoons butter and add cracker crumbs, tossing to coat. In a 2-quart casserole, spread half on the carrots, then half the cheese; repeat.
Pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: swiss ham delights
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix in mustard, Worcestershire and poppy seed.
Split rolls and put spread on both sides of bread. Then add sliced ham and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. These freeze well.

title: chicken philippine style
directions: Marinate chicken in mixture of other ingredients for about 30 minutes.
This can be done in skillet to be used for cooking. Heat on top of stove until it comes to a boil; cover and simmer about 40 minutes or until almost all liquid has evaporated.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes four servings.
Approximate calories per serving:

title: shrimp saute
directions: Stir garlic salt and flour into butter in a large skillet and cook until butter is melted.
Add shrimp.
Cook over medium heat until shrimp turn pink.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat until hot and bubbly.
Serve over rice.

title: shrimp dip appetizer
directions: Mix all.
Hollow out round loaf of pumpernickel bread and fill with dip.
Serve diced bread on the side.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook and stir ground turkey in large skillet until meat is brown and no liquid remains, set aside.
In Dutch oven or large sauce pan, boil water as directed on lasagna noodle package.
Boil noodles for 10 minutes, no more.
Drain in colander.
Rinse under cold water.
Place noodles on a towel to dry (lay them flat and separate).
Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Combine all cheeses, parsley flakes and sugar in a large bowl, mix thoroughly.
Combine tomato sauce with turkey in skillet, mix thoroughly.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place a third of the meat mixture evenly in the bottom of the pan.
Spoon half of the cheese mixture evenly on top of the meat mixture.
Place three lasagna noodles on top of the cheese mixture.
Spoon meat mixture on top of noodles, making sure to cover every bit of the noodles.
Repeat with cheese mixture and so on.
Cover with tin foil.
Bake for 45 minutes, uncover for last 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool for 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 12.

title: chewy sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening in a bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture gradually.
Beat well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender and then drain. Melt butter and pour into casserole dish.
Mix together egg, milk, salt and pepper.
Add drained squash.
Add cracker crumbs, leaving enough to cover top.
Bake in oven for about 20 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: ham salad
directions: Combine ham, celery and eggs.
Add mayonnaise, pickles and catsup.
Toss well.

title: modern corn light bread
directions: Grease loaf pans.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven. Bake in 2 regular loaf pans. Mix all dry ingredients together in large mixing bowl; add milk, then egg, last shortening.
Divide in 2 pans.
Check your oven for timing.
Let cook to light brown.

title: apple salad
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients.
Mix last 3 ingredients and pour over apples, etc.
Stir well and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: oreo cheesecake
directions: Crush 24 cookies and blend with butter.
Press onto bottom only of a 10 inch spring form pan.	Freeze until ready to use. Heat oven to 425°.	Beat cream cheese on low speed of mixer until mixture is smooth.	Beat in sugar and the flour.
Beat in eggs with yolks.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Stir in whipping cream and vanilla.
Spoon 1/3 of the batter into already prepared pan.
Crumble 12 remaining cookies over top. Then spoon remaining batter over the cookies.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 225°, and bake 50 minutes more.

title: sweet potato balls - satsumaimo no chakin-shibori
directions: Peel the potatoes and cut into several pieces.
Soak in water for 10 minutes and drain.
Boil until tender.
Drain, reserving 3 tablespoons of water.
Mash potatoes while hot.
Dissolve the tea in 1 1/2 tablespoons of the reserved water and combine with 1/2 the mashed potatoes.
Divide into 8 portions.
Dissolve the sugar in the remaining water and mix into the other half of the mashed potatoes.
In the center of a small piece of plastic wrap, place one portion each of both kinds of mashed potato; wrap up and twist, using both hands.
Remove wrap.
Makes 8 balls.

title: sand tarts(sandkake)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until almost white.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavoring.
Add flour slowly; do this by hand, as it will be too heavy for the mixer.
Place about 1 teaspoon into sandkake tin and form to shape of tin.
Trim off excess.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly in pans.
Turn upside down and lightly squeeze side of tin to remove sandkake.

title: jane's macaroni and cheese
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown onion until tender.
Add ham and brown lightly.
Add soup, diluted with 1/2 can of water.
Stir in the cooked, drained macaroni.
Stir in cheese until barely melted. Place in baking dish; cover with bread crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Can be served without crumbs and baking.

title: creamy beef-tomato skillet
directions: Brown meat, breaking up meat and pouring off excess fat occasionally.
(Be sure meat is well drained.)
Stir in onion, green pepper, garlic, tomatoes, tomato sauce, macaroni (uncooked), pimento, sugar, chili powder and salt.
Bring to boil; cover. Turn down flame and let simmer 20 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Stir in sour cream. Heat and serve at once.

title: baked chicken sandwiches
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Place 8 slices of bread in a baking pan.
Place about 1/3 cup chicken mixture on bread and cover with second slice.
(If making for next day wrap each in plastic wrap or sandwich bag and freeze or refrigerate.)
When ready to bake, dip the sandwiches in beaten eggs (4 or 5 eggs) and then crushed potato chips.
Bake in preheated oven on Pam-sprayed pan.
Chilled sandwiches bake for 25 minutes at 350° and frozen sandwiches bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Good served with fruit salad or skewered fresh fruit.
Serves 8. Can be expanded for large group.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Pour the hot water over the Jell-O and candy.
Cool, then add applesauce, chopped celery and chopped nuts.

title: acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds.
Place in 2 clear glass baking dishes with 2 tablespoons water on the bottom of each. Microwave on High with the top covered with plastic wrap for 5 minutes.
Turn squash in microwave after 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave and add butter and brown sugar to the cavity.
Divide equally between the two halves.
Cook in microwave covered for 1 to 3 more minutes, testing for doneness.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Bring to a boil. Let cool thoroughly.
Put cucumbers in containers.
Pour syrup mixture over and freeze.
Allow enough time to thaw before serving. "Very good," Sharon says.

title: butter ball cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add beaten egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour which has been sifted with baking powder and salt.
Shape in 2 long rolls.
Cut off pieces the size of a marble.
Dip in granulated sugar; roll in palm of hand until round.
Dip in sugar again and place on ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: caramel rolls(make these the night before you intend to serve)
directions: Grease a Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
Put frozen dinner rolls in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle pudding and brown sugar over the top.
Pour butter over all and sprinkle with nuts.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 4 to 5 minutes and dump out on serving dish.

title: blackberry peach cobbler
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat together liquids.
In a medium bowl add dry ingredients.
Pour in liquid mixture; stir just until moist.
Pour into greased 11 x 13-inch pan.
Top with spoonfuls of batter.
Topping will expand and spread while baking. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
Top with favorite cold topping if desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: rice pudding in double boiler
directions: Put rice in double boiler with milk.
Cook until quite soft. Add raisins and nutmeg.
Cook 20 minutes.
Then add beaten egg with sugar.
Cook 3 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together; put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix together the butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until creamy. Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Mix dry into wet ingredients.
Roll in ball and refrigerate.
Roll out about 1/4 inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken creole
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter.
Add mushrooms, tomatoes, bay leaf, sugar, seasoned salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add chicken and simmer.
Blend cornstarch and water and cook until thickened.
Garnish with parsley and serve.

title: souper sandwiches
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in skillet on medium-high heat until meat is browned.
Drain.
Take off heat and add soup (undiluted) and enough mayonnaise to make a creamy consistency. Spread on buns.

title: apple cider pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with half of pastry; lay aside. Combine cider and sugar in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add apples; cook, uncovered, 8 minutes or until apples are tender. Drain, reserving syrup.
Add enough water to syrup to measure 1 1/3 cups liquid; return syrup mixture and apples to saucepan. Combine cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water, stirring well.
Add to apple mixture.
Stir in cinnamon.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in butter.
Spoon mixture into pastry-lined pie plate.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: bunches of bloodys(may prepare ahead.  serves 25.)
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container.
When ready to serve, mix 1/4 cup mix with 2/3 cup boiling water.

title: potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread 4 cups of potatoes in greased baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour 1/2 of mixture over potatoes.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake for one hour. Uncover and bake 30 to 40 minutes more.

title: baked bourbon-glazed ham
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

Place the ham, fat side up, on a rack in a shallow roasting pan large enough to hold the ham comfortably. Bake in the middle of the oven without basting for 2 hours or until the meat can be easily pierced with a fork or reaches a temperature of 130° to 140°.

title: fettuccine
directions: Boil the noodles until almost done; drain.
Saute the ham and garlic in about 3 tablespoons butter until brown.
Add the noodles and more butter if necessary.
Saute.
Add cream until well coated.
Add seasonings to taste.
Add Parmesan cheese.
If mixture is too dry, add more cream.
You want a fairly heavy sauce.
Fresh mushrooms can also be added along with the ham, if desired.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole combine all ingredients except chicken, butter and seasoning.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice mixture.
Brush chicken with melted butter, salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake, covered, in 375° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Uncover last 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5. Recipe may be doubled for 9 x 13-inch size dish.

title: twinkies cake dessert
directions: Slice Twinkies in half lengthwise and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with half of crushed toffee bars.
Cover with instant pudding and put rest of Twinkies on top of pudding. Cover with Cool Whip and more crushed toffee.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and 1 cup water in medium saucepan; stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring until a little in cold water forms a soft ball (takes about 15 minutes).
Add peanuts; cook until syrup turns golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Add butter and soda, stirring just enough to mix.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet, forming a large square of brittle.
Cool, then break into pieces.

title: wylene's apple dumplings
directions: Peel, quarter and core apples.
Cut each biscuit in half and roll thin.
Place 1/4 apple in each half.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and tuck dough around apple.
Place cut side down
in
9 x 13 x 2 inch pan or casserole dish.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and toss well.
Add the dressings.
Toss together.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: goop(not eatable)
directions: Mix equal parts of liquid starch and glue.
Add a few drops of food coloring.
Hand mix for a while until there is a rubbery consistency.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Add cocoa to 1 cup of sugar and mix well.
Stir in 2 cups milk to make smooth mixture and heat in top of double boiler.
Beat egg yolks.
Add flour, blended with remaining 1/2 cup of milk.
Add salt and stir into milk mixture.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add butter or margarine and vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked pastry shell.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together the shortening and sugar.
Add the egg; beat until creamy.
Add flour, soda and salt to mixture; mix well on low speed.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
No icing is needed.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Separate crabmeat, and blend into cream cheese.
Add onion, horseradish, garlic salt, almonds and milk.
Mix well together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve immediately with crackers.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed except use only 1/2 of water and use the rest with pineapple juice.
Take drained pineapple, brown sugar, cinnamon and coconut.
Mix together.
Spread into pan and add chopped cherries.
Pour on cake mix and bake.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Use electric blender or mixer.
Constant beating to blend the ingredients is the secret to success!
Combine sugar, mustard, salt and celery seed.
Add grated onion.
Gradually add salad oil and cider vinegar, constantly beating.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 c. pecans.
Make into a ball. Roll in pecans.

title: classic meat loaf
directions: Combine soup and water; set aside.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put in tinfoil in baking dish.

title: peanut butter crispy treats(kid's favorite)
directions: Pour corn syrup and sugar into a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture begins to boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies and stir until well coated.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with melted chocolate chips.
Cool, cut and serve.

title: taco sauce
directions: Mix together and add whatever you may like.
Great as a dip with tortilla chips.
Makes an excellent chili sauce.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie crust. Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 325° and cook until brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: white bean soup a la jennifer vail
directions: Melt butter in medium size saucepan over medium-low heat.
Add celery, carrots, onion and garlic.
Stir to mix well.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and cover; simmer 15 minutes for flavors to blend.

title: dried snitz pie
directions: Soak apples in warm water. Cook over low heat until soft. Mash apples and add lemon and sugar. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Cover with top crust. Seal edges. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; lower heat to 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm.

title: ziti bake
directions: Prepare ziti as directed on package; drain and set aside.
In large frying pan, cook beef until well browned; remove from heat and drain.
Stir in Ricotta, then place in large bowl and add Parmesan cheese, parsley, pepper, egg and half of sauce.
Stir until well mixed.
Add ziti and toss gently to coat well.
Spoon mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour remaining sauce evenly over ziti mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Combine 1/2 of shredded cheeses with mixture in bowl.
Place 1/2 of a large serving spoonful of this mixture on each tortilla.
Roll tortillas and place side by side in greased or sprayed baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Cover tortillas with remaining cheeses, starting with Colby.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: south african milk tart
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, oil and egg.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well; add a little milk if necessary. Grease 2 pie plates and press crust in plates.

title: layered salad
directions: Place lettuce, cauliflower and onion in layers.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar and spread over salad layers sealing edges. Sprinkle Bac*Os and cheese over mayonnaise.
Seal with plastic wrap and refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: for sandwich fillings
directions: Add
green pepper and onion to bologna.
Mix with salad dressing.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat the egg whites and salt.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add chocolate chips.
Put on greased cookie sheet(s) in a 375° oven. Turn oven off.
Leave in oven overnight.

title: baked pheasant
directions: Cut pheasant in half.
Place each half on a piece of heavy-duty foil large enough to wrap around loosely and double seam over.
Place 1 tablespoon of butter on top of each.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, a little pepper and parsley.
Wrap each pheasant half leaving space above pheasant, also leaving an opening at one end.
Pour 1/4 cup of beer into opening and seal tightly.
Place foil-wrapped pheasant on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rum raisin balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine 1 cup sugar and remaining ingredients; stir until well blended.
Spoon into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool on a wire rack 10 minutes.
Using damp hands, shape into 1-inch balls; roll in remaining sugar. Store in airtight container.

title: almond joy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Melt almond bark and spread over ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: deep dish pie
directions: Melt margarine in a deep glass baking dish in the microwave. Mix together the sugar, self-rising flour and milk.
Pour batter on top of melted margarine and pour fruit on top of batter.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and evaporated milk to a full boil. Allow to boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Beat and pour in large pan.
Allow it to set overnight.

title: peggy's chicken casserole
directions: Combine bread and cheese.
Dip breast halves in crumb mixture to coat lightly. Arrange in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set remaining crumb mixture aside.

title: franklin nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat eggs well. Mix with butter, sugar and flour. Drench pineapple and cherries with 1 cup flour. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: bread salad
directions: Combine bread cubes, onion and eggs; refrigerate overnight. Next day, add crab, shrimp, celery and mayonnaise to blend. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Drain pineapple, mandarin oranges and cherries.
Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: best pie ever
directions: Add Cool Whip to melted candy bars.
Mix well.
Put into a vanilla wafer crust.
Use remaining Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Mix grated oranges with flour and mix all together with rest of ingredients.
Fold in cranberries, nuts and dates.
Grease tube pan and flour.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Mix 1 cup orange juice and 1 cup sugar together and pour over cake while hot.
Let set until cool, turning over a few times while cooling.

title: cake dessert
directions: Bake cake.
Mix pudding according to box directions.
Mix pineapple with pudding and spread on cake.
Top with Cool Whip if you like.

title: favorite company salad
directions: Cut lettuce into bite size pieces and place in a large salad bowl.
Slice the red onion paper thin and add to the bowl.
Cut the artichoke hearts into small pieces and add to salad.
Add parmesan cheese.
In a small bowl, combine vegetable oil, olive oil and red wine vinegar.
Mix well and pour over salad.
Toss salad well and serve immediately.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix together coconut, sugar and sour cream and put in refrigerator until cake is cooled.
Bake cake mix; make 2 layers and cool.
Split layers and spread coconut mixture between each layer.
Ice cake top and sides with Cool Whip or 7 minute icing. Sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: holiday vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil and salt and bring to a full boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill 24 hours.

title: banana salad
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour.
Add 1 cup milk.
Cook until really thick.
Add peanut butter.
Cool overnight in refrigerator.
Next day mix Dream Whip and 1 cup milk.
Add vanilla.
Beat until stiff. Mix with pudding mixture.
Put a layer of pudding in the bottom of a serving bowl.
Alternate bananas and pudding ending up with pudding.
Sprinkle ground white skinless peanuts on top.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt margarine and white chocolate.
Combine all ingredients. Bake at 350°.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine oats, peanut butter, coconut, cocoa and vanilla, mixing well; set aside.
Combine sugar, milk and butter in a small saucepan, bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Pour over reserved oat mixture, quickly stir to mix well. Immediately drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper lined baking sheets.
Let cool.
Carefully remove from wax paper to serve.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: apricot glazed ham
directions: Score surface of ham, making diamond shapes 1/4-inch deep. Insert a clove in each diamond.
Place ham on rack in a shallow roasting pan; pour ginger ale into pan. Loosely cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
In small bowl, combine the spreadable fruit, brown sugar, mustard and ginger; brush some over ham. Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, brushing occasionally with glaze.
Serve with remaining glaze. Yield: 16 servings.

title: beef provencale
directions: In a skillet, heat butter until lightly brown.
Add meat; brown well on all sides.
Sprinkle with half the salt and pepper.
Reduce heat; cover and let meat cook about 10 minutes.
Turn once during cooking.
Remove meat; cover with foil.
Add water to pan.
Heat and scrape drippings; strain juices.
Peel potatoes; slice thinly. Layer into a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining salt and pepper.
Pour pan juices over.

title: pineapple zucchini cake
directions: Cream eggs; add sugar and oil.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and soda into creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple and zucchini.
Add nuts and drained raisins.
Spoon into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use toothpick test.

title: potato appetizers
directions: Put potatoes on greased jelly roll pan and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn after 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and place various toppings on potatoes.
Return to oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: platte county pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine and beat the eggs, flour and sugar.
Add melted butter, vanilla extract and chocolate chips. Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese and 1 cup sugar; fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on the cooled pretzel crust. Dissolve strawberry jello in 2 cups boiling water; stir in frozen strawberries.
Put in refrigerator for 10 minutes, then spread over second layer.
Refrigerate until set.

title: potato dish
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix 1 stick oleo, soup, sour cream, salt, pepper, onion, cheese and potatoes.
Place in large baking dish. Combine corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted oleo; spread on top of potato mixture.

title: chocolate pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar.
Beat in eggs until smooth. Stir in flour, salt, cocoa, baking soda and vanilla.
Roll 2 teaspoons of the dough
into a ball for each cookie.
Put into ungreased baking sheet, 1 inch apart.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken supreme casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into large 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Cover with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese and then sprinkle paprika to taste. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until "bubbly hot".

title: my mom's potato salad dressing
directions: Mix in small saucepan over medium heat the vinegar, sugar and egg yolks.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Cool, then add an equal amount of Hellmann's mayonnaise.
For a large bowl of salad, double recipe.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and add peppers and soup. Place layer of chips in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Alternate with chicken and soup mixture.
Bake until hot, then top with shredded sharp Cheddar cheese and melt.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel and chop fruit.
Add chopped pecans and condensed milk. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
For more color, leave peeling on one apple.

title: chicken-artichoke casserole
directions: In a large bowl, quarter the artichoke hearts. Add the diced chicken, soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Stir to mix all ingredients. Place in a 9 x 13 casserole dish that has been greased or sprayed with Pam. On the top, scatter the grated Cheddar cheese. Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: chicken can-can
directions: Cook chicken done; debone and set aside, removing all fat and skin.
Cook the rice and set aside.
In a wok or nonstick deep, heavy saucepan, mix the chicken, rice, soups, peas, water and seasoning to taste.
You may also add cut up mushrooms to taste.

title: double fudge saucepan brownies
directions: Heat oven at 325°.
Grease 9-inch square baking pan.
In medium saucepan, combine sugar, butter and water.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add one cup chocolate chips, stirring until melted.
Stir in eggs and vanilla until blended.
Gradually add flour mixture, blending well.
Stir in remaining chocolate chips and nuts, if desired.
Pour batter in prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until brownies pull away from side of pan.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and cherry pie filling; mix until well blended.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake springs back when touched. Frost when cool.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Cut lobster in large pieces, heat slowly in butter for 5 minutes.
Add wine and simmer slowly until wine is reduced.
Beat cream and eggs together.
Add lobster and seasonings.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened (low flame).
It thickens in about 5-10 minutes, like a white sauce.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to box.
Pour 1/2 batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels in milk and margarine.
Pour over cake.
Grate chocolate bar and sprinkle over caramel.
Add nuts.
Pour rest of batter over all.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer in order given.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Out of this world delicious!
Also mouth-watering good!!

title: 7 layered salad
directions: In a 9 x 13 pan, layer lettuce, eggs, peas and onions.
Mix the Miracle Whip, sour cream and Hidden Valley dressing mix and spread over the top.
Sprinkle with cheddar cheese and bacon. Refrigerate overnight.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: Brown beef.
Put all ingredients in deep casserole.
Cover tightly and bake 5 hours at 225°.

title: oatmeal chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add salt, baking soda and baking powder to flour.
Mix well.
Then add to creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal slowly.
The mixture will be stiff.
Add chocolate morsels and nuts.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: walnut apple pie
directions: In a bowl, toss apples with lemon juice. Combine the sugars, nuts, tapioca, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add to apples and toss to coat. Let stand for 15 minutes. Line a 9-inch pie plate with bottom pastry. Trim even with edge. Add apple mixture. Dot with butter. Roll out remaining pastry to fit top of pie. Place over filling. Trim, seal and flute edges. Cut slits in top. Cover edges loosely with foil. Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until crust is brown and filling is bubbly. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
In a medium-size bowl, beat together butter and peanut butter until blended. Beat in sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture with a pastry blender until fine crumbs form.
Add milk and stir until mixture is moistened.
Turn into a greased loaf pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for approximately 55 to 60 minutes.
Store in plastic wrap or foil.
Kids love this!!

title: jello cheese fruit pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add lemon juice and cool until syrupy.
Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add Jell-O to cheese mixture and mix well.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Add fruit (same flavor as Jell-O used).
Fill cooled pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: omelet ol
directions: Combine sour cream and salsa in a small saucepan; cook over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Keep warm.
Whisk together eggs and milk; set aside.
Heat a 6 inch omelet pan or heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add 1 tsp butter, and rotate pan to coat.
Add half of egg mixture.
As mixture starts to cook, gently lift edges of omelette with a spatula, and tilt pan so uncooked portion flows underneath.
Sprinkle with half each of bacon, tomato, green chiles, and cheese; fold in half, and transfer to a serving place. Repeat procedure.
Serve with sour cream mixtures and avocado slices.

title: coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie crusts.
Cook for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.

title: colorful corn salad
directions: Mix vegetables with as much mayonnaise as desired.
Salt and pepper to taste and chill.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix juice with cornstarch and heat until thickened.
Add oleo and spices.
Mix lightly with apples.
Fill pastry-lined pan. Cover with top crust.
Cut slit in pie.
Bake at 450° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Place cookie sheet under pie to catch overflow.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken stroganoff casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except rice.
Mix well.
Put into lightly buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: potato casserole
directions: Stir together and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: cheese-mushroom cups
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium skillet, saute onions and mushrooms in margarine.
Remove from heat; stir in cheeses, parsley, egg yolks, oregano, salt and pepper.
Trim crusts from bread; cut each slice into 4 equal squares.
Roll pieces flat with rolling pin.
Dip bread squares into melted margarine.
Fit into mini-muffin cups.
Fill each cup with mushroom-cheese mixture. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 32 appetizers.
(Can be prepared ahead of time, frozen and reheated just before serving.)

title: angel cake dessert
directions: Tear angel cake into pieces; place in bowl and add crushed pineapple on cake.
Add pudding; top with whipped topping.
Add maraschino cherries, drained and dry on top.

title: yellow punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar, juices and tap water; mix well.
Freeze, stirring occasionally.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: stuffed breast of chicken
directions: Prepare 1 package of Stove Top dressing mix as directed; add 1 egg when water is dissolved and mix.
Stuff chicken breast and place in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake for 40 minutes. Pour heated cream of mushroom soup on top of chicken before serving.

title: mom's peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk until form a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Beat slightly until mixed.
Pour into a buttered pan; use a 10 x 13 pan until cool.

title: chili-burger supper
directions: Brown meat in electric skillet.
Add soups and 2 cans of water. Bring to boil and add macaroni.
Cook until done.
Turn off heat and break cheese in triangles.
Lay on top of meat/macaroni mixture.

title: flowerpot dirt cake
directions: In our family, a dish is named after the person who first introduces it to the family.
This one has been a favorite for years.
It will keep well in the refrigerator for a week if the kids aren't home.

title: frying pan cookies
directions: Melt butter in frying pan on low heat.
Mix sugar, eggs and chopped dates in a bowl.
Add to pan.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add Rice Krispies.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Break spaghetti in 3-inch lengths and cook in large amount of water; drain well.
In Dutch oven, cook meat, onion and green pepper until meat is brown.
Sprinkle with salt.
Gradually stir in soups, milk and 2 cups cheese.
Divide cooked spaghetti evenly in two 13 x 9 x 2-inch pans.
Into each pan, stir half of soup and meat mixture; sprinkle remaining 2 cups of cheese on top of each. Bake, uncovered at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves 20.
This is great for a dish to take out to a Pot Luck or covered dish dinner.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cook chicken; remove skin and cut meat off bones.
Add corn and rivels.
Let cook for awhile, then add chopped eggs.
Let simmer for several hours.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well and cut into strips.
Combine rest of ingredients in plastic bag.
Add potatoes and shake to coat. Spread strips on 2 cookie sheets in a single layer.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and tender, stirring once.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and butter (melted); mix well. Add flour. Mix well. Add vanilla. Add fruit, raisins and nuts; mix.
Pour into ungreased angel food cake pan.
Steam in a 6-quart canner with rack in bottom for 3 to 4 hours. Take off stove.
Remove from pan.
Cool overnight.
Remove from pan.

title: basic tomato sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in a little Crisco oil until lightly brown.
Pour into large pot.
Add all remaining ingredients. Simmer over low flame for 3 to 4 hours.
This sauce keeps well frozen.

title: slaw
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Mix the cabbage, pepper and onions with the dressing.
Put in jar, seal tightly.
Let stand overnight (5 days is best).
This is good served with the Pinto Bean Casserole.

title: beer batter
directions: Combine flour, cornstarch, Bisquick, beer,
salt to taste, and mix well.
Coat cleaned, deveined shrimp, fresh scallops, bite-size cauliflower, or whatever you wish, with the batter and deep fry.

title: renee's dip
directions: Mix together.
Chill overnight or longer.
Serve with crackers, chips
or raw vegetables.

title: candied chicken wings
directions: Place cleaned and disjointed chicken wings in foil-lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Combine honey, soy sauce, brown sugar, garlic and ketchup.
Pour over chicken and bake, uncovered, turning and basting every 15 minutes with sauce mixture.

title: yummy casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain off fat.
Cook macaroni according to directions and drain.
Put first four ingredients plus sauteed onions into 3-quart casserole dish and mix well with 3/4 of shredded cheese.
Add other 1/4 cheese to top of casserole.
Cover dish and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease tube pan.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each. Stir soda into 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Stir salt into remaining milk. Add flour to butter and sugar mixture, alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry and fold into batter.
Pour into pan and bake 1 hour and 45 minutes or until cracks on top.
Cool in pan.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, margarine, milk and salt.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix well. Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.

title: karo nut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pie shell.
Pour into shell. Let stand 5 minutes so nuts will rise.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife blade inserted in center comes out clean.
(For Country Fair or holiday pie, turn nuts all right side up for better looking pie.)

title: deviled egg casserole
directions: In a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch casserole arrange deviled egg halves, filled side up.
In medium saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour. Add milk.
Cook and stir until thick and smooth.
Add soup and blend.
Stir in lemon juice, ham and mushrooms.
Pour over deviled eggs.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Bake for 20 minutes or until bubbly hot at 325°.

title: asparagus vinaigrette
directions: Cut asparagus into
pieces
and cook until barely done. Drain and put in iced water.
Mix sugar and vinegar; add water and salt to taste. Add Good Seasons.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter, milk, sugar and vanilla, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crust pie shells and freeze.
Thaw somewhat before serving.

title: quick cubed steak
directions: Lay raw cubed steak in pan.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over steak.
Mix mushroom soup and water.
Pour over steak.
Bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) or 2 square pans (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine cocoa and baking soda.
Blend in 1/3 cup melted butter or margarine.
Add boiling water; stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup butter or margarine.
Stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt and blend.
Pour into pan or pans and bake until it begins to pull away from sides of pan.

title: rice salad
directions: *Save oil from artichoke hearts to mix with mayo for dressing.

title: spicy wings
directions: Wash and place wings in large Ziploc bag.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over wings.
Seal bag and refrigerate overnight.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: aunt myrtle's sweet potato pudding
directions: Peel and grate potato in milk.
Add other ingredients and bake at 350° until firm.

title: lettuce-cauliflower salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Put in an airtight container. Refrigerate overnight. Toss just before serving.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Divide crescent rolls into 4 sections.
Pinch seams together and roll to desired thickness.
Layer ham, mustard and cheese; roll into jelly roll form.
Slice and roll in sesame seed.
Bake on lightly greased baking sheet at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until light brown.

title: strawberry lush dessert
directions: Blend together flour and butter.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until light brown.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle with the buttered bread crumbs in large greased (or Pam) pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Place scallops in dish.
Mix crackers and crumbs together; place over scallops.
Melt butter and add.
Drizzle half and half over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rosy glow punch
directions: Combine red punch, grapefruit and limeade concentrate and mix well.
Chill and add soda water just before serving.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: In
large
bowl,
heat	milk,
peanut
butter,	egg and vanilla
until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Preheat
oven to 350°.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on baking sheet and flatten with fork crisscross (fork dipped in sugar).
Bake 6 to 8 minutes. Solid milk chocolate kiss can be pressed
in
center after baked.
Do not flatten with fork. These are called Peanut Blossoms.

title: edible play dough
directions: Use peanut shells to decorate with faces and place on fingers.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Saute the onions in butter until tender. Combine onions, sour cream, chicken soup and cooking sherry. Add spaghetti.
Stir in diced turkey.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle top with Romano cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and soak with Kahlua or juice.
Prepare mousse and set aside.
In very large glass bowl, crumble 1/2 of chocolate cake, 1/2 chocolate mousse, 1/2 Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with candy bar pieces.
Repeat layers.
Chill and serve.

title: toothpaste
directions: Mix baking soda and salt. Add peroxide, mixing until paste of desired consistency is formed.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package. Cool. Mix pudding as directed. Crumble cake. Layer cake, pudding, pineapple, pie filling, Cool Whip and chopped nuts in punch bowl or large clear glass bowl. Chill. Good dessert for large crowd.

title: grandma's jelly roll
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients (flour, sugar, salt and baking powder).
Add the oil, water, egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites stiff with cream of tartar.
Fold beaten egg white mixture into batter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Place on wax paper lined pan.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter; do not stir.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over crumbs; do not stir. Sprinkle coconut then nuts; do not stir.
Pour condensed milk over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: frosting cake
directions: Mix cake, eggs, water and oil together well. Add frosting, coconut and pecans. Flour pan well. Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: seasoned pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper.
Spread mustard to one side.
Fry chops in oil with mustard side fried first.
Use fried oil to make flour gravy.
Add rice soup, place pork chops in gravy and simmer until ready to serve.

title: double marble cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Prepare cake batter according to package directions using eggs, oil and water.
Stir 1/2 cup of chocolate chips into chocolate batter.
Spoon vanilla and chocolate batters into prepared pan; swirl as directed on package.
Bake 33 to 38 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 5 minutes.
Gently spread Marshmallow Creme over warm cake.
In small saucepan over low, heat remaining 1/2 cup chips.
Swirl through Marshmallow Creme.
Cool thoroughly.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together for four minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured baking pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: taco pizza
directions: In medium skillet, brown beef until crumbly; drain.
Mix in taco seasoning and water.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
For each pizza, spread 1/2 taco sauce on crust.
Top each with 1/2 meat mixture, onion, olives and cheese.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
Makes 2 pizzas.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cook on High 4 minutes; add roasted peanuts.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes until light brown.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well and microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Gently stir in 1 tablespoon baking soda until light and foamy.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine butter, salt, powdered sugar and flour.
Mix well. Press mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° preheated oven about 15 to 20 minutes until browned.
Combine 1/2 cup flour and sugar, then mix in eggs and lemon juice.
Pour into slightly cooled crust and bake 25 minutes or until set at 350°.
When removed from oven, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: super orange party jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sherbet.
When partially set, add whipped cream and oranges.
Chill until firm. May be served as dessert or delicious salad.
Serves 10, if you're lucky!

title: swedish coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour

Bundt pan. Use large mixing bowl to cream oleo, sugar and eggs. Drain cherry juice into this mixture. Chop cherries, keeping separate. Add milk and vanilla to mixture. Put flour and baking powder in sifter. Sift in separate container. Add flour and baking powder mix to mixture slowly with mixer running. Mix well. Stir in nuts and cherries. Pour in pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: frost on the pumpkin cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs in large mixing bowl.
Combine dry ingredients; mix with oil mixture.
Stir in pumpkin; beat well. Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans or one 13 x 9-inch sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (layer) or 40 to 50 minutes (sheet pan).
Cool.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cut chicken into smaller pieces; using a food processor, chop the chicken to the consistency of ground beef.
Chop the cabbage (approximately 2 pounds) to the consistency of cole slaw.
Take 2 nests of the bean threads from package; soak them in hot water to soften the threads, then cut into 2-inch strips.

title: thick fruit salad dressing
directions: Put oil in refrigerator overnight.
Dissolve sugar, mustard, salt and paprika in 1/4 cup vinegar.
Add oil to mixture slowly and beat 3 minutes until thick.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: mitchell's favorite microwave sticky buns
directions: In an 8-inch round glass dish, mix together the butter, brown sugar, water and cinnamon.
Cook on High for 1 minute; stir until butter melts.
Cut the biscuits into quarters and place in mixture.
Stir carefully to coat.
Push biscuits towards outsides of dish and place cup in center.
Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Let mix set 1 hour before serving.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour.
Combine bread, milk and cream.
Beat eggs.
Stir in sugar; add to mixture.
Stir in vanilla, nutmeg, cinnamon, butter and raisins.
Pour into buttered 2-quart dish.
Set in a larger pan of water.
Use Brandy Sauce.

title: orange crunch cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and press into two 9-inch pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake as it says.
Add orange peel and lemon peel.
Pour batter over crunch layer and bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean, about 35 minutes.
Cool, then frost.

title: chocolate trix clusters
directions: Put chocolate bark in microwave for 2 minutes on high.
Stir chocolate and add Trix and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let cool.
Yields 3 dozen clusters.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Mix and let rise until doubled in size.
Knead.
Make into rolls and let rise again.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: garbage snack
directions: Combine cereal, raisins and peanuts in large container. Combine butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips in a saucepan and melt.
Pour over mixture.
Pour powdered sugar in clean kitchen garbage bag.
Add above mixture and shake until well coated.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in 2 quart round casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda, salt, butter, vanilla and egg. Beat at medium speed 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in the oats and, if desired, one of the optional ingredients.
Press the mixture into the pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over the dough.
Press in slightly.

title: *blueberry batter cake
directions: Line a well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with blueberries. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Cream sugar and butter together; add milk alternately with flour, baking powder and salt, which have been sifted together.
Pour this batter evenly over blueberries. Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Sprinkle over the top of the cake. Pour boiling water over all and bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour. Serves 9.

title: south of border casserole
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Combine beans and olives.
Layer in a casserole dish one cup corn chips, cheese mixture, one cup corn chips and chile-olive mixture.
Sprinkle with one-half cup corn chips.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove and sprinkle with one-half cup grated cheese.
Place in oven again until cheese melts.

title: icebox pudding
directions: Melt chocolate with 1 tablespoon water in a double boiler. Beat yolks of eggs well, 1 tablespoon sugar and melted chocolate; fold in egg whites which have been whipped. Line 7/9 dish with wax paper. Put ladyfingers on bottom and pour mixture over first layer of ladyfingers; cover with another layer of ladyfingers and the rest of the chocolate mixture. Put in the refrigerator overnight. Cover the top with Saran Wrap. Serve with whipped cream.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Boil cauliflower, carrots and onion until tender.
Drain water.
Cook potatoes in small amount of water until done, then mash.
Add potatoes, milk and seasonings to cauliflower mixture. Heat through, then add cheese and ham and heat until cheese is melted.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Cook all but pecans and marshmallows in a double boiler for 5 minutes.
When cold, add pecans and marshmallows.
Pour over fruit.

title: mocha chocolate frosting
directions: Dissolve cocoa in coffee.
Add butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Add sugar gradually until of spreading consistency.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain lima or yellow butter beans and kidney beans.
Fry bacon very crisp.
Brown ground turkey and onion in the bacon fat until soft.
Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 325° or put in a crock-pot and cook for 5 or 6 hours on high.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken and rice dinner
directions: Boil chicken and remove from pan, reserving liquid. Boil rice in this reserved liquid for added flavor. Strip chicken from bones. Combine all ingredients.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until done.

title: cashew brittle
directions: Place cashews on cookie sheet and put in low oven and heat slightly.
Put sugar, water and syrup in saucepan on medium heat. When it boils up for the first time, wash sugar crystals down the side of pan with stirring spoon.
Stir in butter.
Cook to 310°, stirring gently with thermometer.
Take pan from heat.
Stir in warm nuts, soda and flavoring.
Pour onto greased baking sheet and spread out.
When it has cooled slightly, loosen it from sheet with long knife and turn it over and stretch it as thin as possible with buttered hands.
Let cool at room temperature until it's hard and brittle.
Break in pieces and store in closed container.

title: western egg omelet
directions: Beat eggs well.
Pour in milk; beat until mixed.
Add salt and pepper.
Saute onions and peppers until soft.
Heat fry pan; pour in egg mixture and milk.
Sprinkle in salt and black pepper.
Fry in bacon drippings until brown on both sides.
Make sure onions, green pepper, cheese and bacon is added before you fold over egg mixture.
Let stand 1 minute; then serve.

title: hello dolly squares
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan on low heat.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread graham cracker crumbs evenly over butter. Sprinkle coconut evenly over graham cracker crumbs.
Add a layer of chopped nuts.
Sprinkle chocolate bits over nuts.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over the top.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Allow to cool to room temperature.
Cut into small squares.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: orange salad
directions: Bring to a boil pineapple and sugar.
Add Jell-O and 2 cups cold water.
Refrigerate until jelly stage.
Add grated cheese, nuts and Cool Whip.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix hot water and jello until dissolved.
Stir in pineapple and pie filling.
Congeal in a long narrow dish in refrigerator. For topping, mix cream cheese, sour cream and sugar well.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Spread over congealed mixture. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: sour cream yeast rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until butter melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Let stand for 5 minutes; stir in sour cream mixture and egg.
Gradually add flour to yeast mixture, mixing well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Punch dough down and divide in half.
Roll each half into a 9 to 12-inch circle on floured surface.
Cut each circle in 12-inch wedges.
Roll each wedge, jelly roll fashion, beginning at wide end.
Place on greased baking sheet, point side down.
Cover and leave in warm place (85°), free from draft, for 1 hour or double in size.
Brush with egg white.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 2 dozen.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain and chop artichokes.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly and top is golden.
Serve with wheat crackers and pumpernickel bread mini-loaf.

title: clam dip in sheepherder bread loaf
directions: Mix in order given.
Chill for 1 day.
When ready to serve, cut top off of bread.
Hollow out and fill with dip.
Serve with bread cubes.
You may use a loaf of French bread cut in cubes for extra bread.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Stir dates, pecans and soda into hot water; set aside to cool. Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add egg and beat well.
Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with fruit-nut mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 28 ounce fruit cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in cans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool on wire racks.
Yield: 2 loaves.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Layer: 1/2 peas, 1/2 chopped pimento, 1/2 boiled eggs and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat.
Put soup and Pet milk on stove and simmer about a minute.
Pour over casserole.
Put layer of bread crumbs on top. Put in oven and brown.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, then chocolate syrup and flour.
Mix.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch glass dish at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: wild rose salad
directions: Heat soup and 1/2 cup of water to very hot, but not boiling. Soften gelatin in cold water, then add to hot soup.
Add cream cheese, crumbled, to hot soup.
Beat until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into swirl molds.
Serves 14.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients except ham together.
Spread on one ham slice at a time.
Roll up and fasten with toothpicks at 1/2-inch intervals.
Put in refrigerator to harden, then slice each rolled-up ham slice in 1/2-inch slices.

title: pecan bars
directions: Blend and put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Put baking powder in with the last cup of flour.
Add vanilla and lemon flavorings.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for the first 1/2 hour, then decrease to 300° for another 45 minutes.
Do not peek.

title: sourdough carrot cake
directions: Stir together
the
flour,
sugar, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Shred
enough carrots to make 2 cups.
Add carrots, oil, sourdough starter and eggs to the flour mixture. Mix until moistened.	Stir in walnuts.
Beat until well mixed. Pour into a greased 12-inch Dutch
oven.
Bake	at 325° for 55 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: buckwheat pancakes
directions: *Sour milk can be made with 2 cups milk and 2 tablespoons vinegar.

title: ausukys
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix and knead with hands.
Keep adding flour to right consistency.
Roll, cut into strips and tie into knot.
Fry in hot Crisco.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: old-fashioned cream soda
directions: Put cream in an 8 ounce glass with vanilla, corn syrup and fill to top of glass with chilled club soda.
Serves 1.

title: creole sauce
directions: Cook onions, green peppers and butter until tender, then add the tomato sauce, chopped mushrooms, water, pepper and garlic salt.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with fish or meat loaf.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: pan o' pizza
directions: Let dough rise according to package directions.
Press sausage into dough that has been placed into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. (Sausage will help hold dough to the edge of the pan.)
Spread with pizza sauce.
Top with Provolone cheese slices, then onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until crust is lightly browned.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in an airtight container.
Pour oil to a depth of 1-inch in skillet.
Heat to 360° over medium-high heat.
Mix egg and milk in a small bowl.
Add 1 cup funnel cake mix.
Beat with fork until smooth.
Holding finger under funnel opening, pour 1/4 of the batter into funnel.
Allow batter to pour from funnel into hot oil, moving funnel in a circle to form a spiral shape.
Fry one minute.
Turn cake and continue frying until golden brown.
Remove to paper towels to drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: enchiladas
directions: Fully cook meat and let simmer.

title: meat balls 3
directions: Mix first five ingredients well and form into balls. Refrigerate overnight.
Mix other ingredients well and pour over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork 'n sauerkraut
directions: Combine all above ingredients in a 6-quart pot.
Add enough water just to barely cover ingredients.
Bring to boil; lower heat to a simmer for about 3 hours, or until pork is very tender. Season to taste, if desired.
Delicious served over mashed potatoes and with steamed buttered baby carrots and rye bread.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown ground turkey and drain.
Add barbecue sauce and sugar. Place 1 biscuit in a muffin cup.
Press dough up sides to edges of cup.
Spoon meat mixture into cup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
