directions: Mix sausage, hamburger, bread and Lipton onion soup mix.
Make into small meatballs (size of walnuts). Put under broiler or cook in frying pan (meatballs).
Mix ketchup, apricot nectar, vinegar, sugar, mustard, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce in slow cooker or in a pan for 10 minutes.
Add meatballs and simmer.

title: tipton's beef hash
directions: Put half of sliced onions in the bottom of crock-pot.
Add beef, cloves, lemon pepper, remaining onions, vinegar and water. Cook on low for 12 hours; stir occasionally.
Remove most of liquid.
Add brown sugar and barbecue sauce.
Cook for 6 hours stirring occasionally.
Remove cloves as you find them and as much fat as possible.
Note:
Great over rice or on a bun.

title: dirt
directions: Mix together prepared pudding and cool whip.
In another bowl blend sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Mix all together.
Crush Oreos.
In a clean flower pot, spoon a layer of pudding mixture and then crushed Oreos, alternating layers with Oreos on top.

title: cool 'n easy pie
directions: Stir boiling water into Jell-O in bowl for 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Mix water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir into Jell-O until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours until firm.
Garnish with additional whipped topping.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Place broccoli on paper towel and drain.
Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot. Add carrot and onion.
Saute 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broccoli, croutons and next four ingredients.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yields 5 servings. Serving size is 1 cup.

title: bailey's irish creme(liqueur)
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine the sweetened milk, all-purpose cream or light cream and instant coffee crystals. Cook and stir over medium heat until coffee crystals are dissolved.
Gradually stir about half of the mixture into the beaten egg yolk until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Irish whiskey and Hershey's syrup.
Cool mixture.
Divide into 3 decorative containers with tight fitting lids.
Store in fridge (keeps for 2 months in fridge).
Serve on the rocks, in coffee or over ice cream.

title: polish sausage and sauerkraut stew
directions: In Dutch oven combine sauerkraut, soup, water and brown sugar. Stir in sausage, potatoes and onion.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in shredded cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: white christmas cake
directions: Combine candied fruits, coconut, raisins, almonds and orange rind in a large bowl.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt over fruit.
Mix well.
Cream margarine with sugar in medium bowl.
Beat in eggs; stir in apple and orange juice.
Pour over fruit mixture; fold and mix thoroughly.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 8-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 3 hours.
Cool completely in pan.
On serving day, put on an Orange Glaze.
Makes an 8-inch round cake.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and 7-Up alternately.
Add flavoring.
Preheat oven and bake at 325° about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: holiday fruit drops
directions: Sift and measure flour; add spices and soda.
Sift 2 or 3 times to mix well.
Save some flour to put over fruits and nuts before adding to mixture.
Cream butter; add sugar and cream well. Add beaten eggs and flour alternately with milk and brandy. Last, fold in fruit and nut mixture.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 275° oven until lightly browned.

title: apple betty(diabetics)
directions: Combine bread crumbs, margarine, brown sugar replacement, cinnamon and salt in a bowl.
Toss to mix.
Arrange layers of crumb mixture and apples alternately in eight lightly greased individual baking dishes.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve hot or cold.
Yield:
8 servings.
Exchange:
serving:
1 starch/bread.
Calories:
1 serving = 73 calories.

title: cabin monsters
directions: Mix ingredients and drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Shred crab meat and add all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: mother's crumb cake
directions: Don't use mixer!
Mix sugar, flour, shortening and baking powder.
Mix this by hand until crumbly.
Save 1 cup for top of cake.
Beat eggs and add milk, then beat all together by hand. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, until cracks appear on top.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Combine Ranch dressing and oil; add dill, garlic powder and lemon pepper.
Pour over crackers and stir.
Toast in warm oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: date nut cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except coconut, dates and pecans.
Mix in coconut, dates and pecans and divide dough in half.
Cut each half in 13 equal pieces.
Roll into balls and place in lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press flat with fork.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Watch carefully to keep from burning on bottom. (Calories:
155 per each 2 cookies.)

title: peachy sorbet cake
directions: Drain peaches, reserve liquid.
Reserve 14 peaches.
Blend remaining peach slices and lemon juice in electric blender until smooth; set aside.
Add water to reserve syrup to make 1 1/2 c. Heat syrup and 1 cup sugar to boiling.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring occasionally; cool.
Finely roll 42 wafers.
Combine crumbs, remaining sugar and margarine; press into bottom of greased and waxed paper lined round pan.
Stand remaining wafers around edge of pan; freeze.
Stir peach mixture into syrup; pour into prepared crust.
Freeze several hours.
Place reserved peach slices on cake.
Freeze overnight.
Remove from pan to plate; let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: deep fried biscuits
directions: In a bowl, mix flour, sugar and lemon rind.
Gently cut in the butter.
Add brandy and water; mix in with minimum of kneading. Wrap up in foil and refrigerate for 1 1/2 hours.
Roll out thinly; cut in 2-inch squares and place on a floured tray.
Cover and refrigerate.
Deep fry in hot oil.
Drain; dust with icing sugar.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cocoa suisse
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl; blend well.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 2 cups of mix.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers, onions and salt with cold water and ice cubes.
Let set about 3 hours.
Do not use metal container.
Mix sugar, cider vinegar, turmeric and celery seed and simmer 30 minutes.
Pour cold water off cucumbers, pack in jar and cover with hot liquid.
Process 10 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine corn, egg yolks and melted butter.
In a jar, combine sugar, milk, flour and salt.
Shake until dissolved.
Add to corn mixture.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: orange coconut  muffins
directions: In large bowl, stir together dry ingredients.
Blend sour cream, eggs and oranges in small bowl.
Stir into dry ingredients along with nuts until all ingredients are evenly blended.
Spoon into buttered muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove from muffin tin and cool. Makes 12 to 16 muffins.

title: pasta fazioli
directions: Slice carrots and celery; cover with water.
When soft, add tomato sauce and water (use own judgement).
Season.
While that is cooking, boil water for ditalini and cook ditalini only for a few minutes.
While ditalini is cooking, add kidney beans to sauce mixture.
Drain ditalini and add it to tomato sauce mixture.
Let cook.

title: filled chip cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box; set aside.
Mix together well cream cheese, sugar and egg.
Fold chocolate chips into the cream cheese mixture.
Fill cupcake cups 3/4 full with cake batter.
Add 1 large tablespoon of cream cheese/chocolate chip mixture to each cupcake.
Bake according to directions on cake mix box.

title: ground beef and rice
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onions.
Blend soup, sherry, mushrooms (using liquid) and garlic salt; pour over meat. Cook over medium heat for 45 minutes.
Or, cover and bake at 350°. Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: super burgers
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Stir in tomato soup, mustard and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring now and then.
Serve on hamburger rolls.
Makes 6 servings.

title: gourmet chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast in bacon.
Pull apart chipped beef and place in bottom of casserole pan.
Put chicken on top of beef. Combine sour cream, soup, sherry and mushrooms; pour over all. Bake, uncovered, 2 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: *shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, cutting Crisco into mixture. After taking out some for top crust, add raisins, molasses, hot water and soda.
Place batter in unbaked pie crusts.
Place balance of crumbs on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Test pie with toothpick by inserting it into the center; if toothpick comes out without filling on it, the pie is done.

title: barbecued beef patties
directions: Moisten crumbs with milk.
Add meat, salt and pepper.
Shape into 4 patties.
Place in baking dish.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over patties.
Serve with baked potato.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: green beans and tomatoes(a low carb recipe)
directions: Wash beans, trim ends, cut into 1 1/2 inch pieces.
Put in boiling water, boil about 4-5 minutes, just until crunchy.
Drain, drop in ice water. Drain after cooled.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook breasts and cut into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips over top.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions fine.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 10 minutes. Drain.
Cover again with hot water and let come to a boil.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain dry and add salt, vinegar and sugar.
Cook for 15 minutes and pack hot in sterilized jars.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Cook peas, carrots and beans until tender.
Combine with chestnuts and mushrooms.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in greased casserole except 1 tablespoon butter and 1/4 cup crumbs which are sprinkled on top of corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs, soda, salt, salad oil and juice from fruit cocktail, then add the fruit and mix.
Pour into a large, greased and floured cake pan.
Sprinkle about 1/2 cup Angel Flake coconut over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Have ready the following topping and pour over the hot cake.

title: potato supreme
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on; cook in salt water.
Refrigerate overnight.
Peel and grate coarsely.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Put in 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple coconut snowballs
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Combine sugar and butter.
Beat on medium until well blended.
Add egg; mix into pineapple.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Add coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine meat, onion, beaten egg, crumbs, milk, sugar and seasonings; mix thoroughly.
Shape into small balls and roll in flour.
Fry in hot fat until brown on all sides.
Remove from pan and set aside.
In same pan, add light cream.
Mix a tablespoonful with 1/3 cup of water and add.
Stir until thick.
Season with 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon pepper.
Add meat balls.
Cover and cook twenty minutes.
Serves 4.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in saucepan over medium-low heat or in microwave for 1 minute and 30 seconds at 70% power. Stir in cereal. Put powdered sugar in brown paper bag. Add coated cereal and shake.

title: sour cream pound cake 2
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at the time.
Add flour and soda.
Add sour cream and flavoring.
Bake at 325 for 25 minutes.
Decrease temperature to 300 and bake for 45 more minutes.
Do not open the oven door.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onions, then drain excess fat.
In casserole dish, first put in beef and onions. Next, add a layer of corn.
Next, add a layer of mashed potatoes. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes until potatoes are browned.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix together and chill overnight.

title: egg casserole
directions: Season each fillet with salt, pepper and season salt. Add 3 teaspoons margarine, sliced, over fish.
Place prepared fillet on foil and seal.
Place on pan in oven and bake 30 minutes at 350° or until fish flakes.
Open foil and broil a few minutes until golden.

title: refreshing orange drink
directions: Put all ingredients in blender until ice is crushed.
May substitute any flavor soda and juice concentrate.

title: russian (flat) pancakes(makes 9 servings)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and salt.
Slowly stir in 1 cup of flour until batter is smooth.
Put 1 teaspoon Crisco or oil in hot cast-iron frying pan. Pour batter in slowly, tilting pan to make a very thin pancake.
Put in oil before each pancake.
Makes 9 thin 8-inch pancakes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and marshmallow cream together. Add lemon juice.
Mix and chill.
Use any fruit you like.

title: spanish rice with pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Slowly brown chops about 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain excess fat.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix the dried fruit, oil and baking soda with boiling water; let cool.
Beat in sugar, flour and egg.
Turn into well oiled 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chops creole
directions: Flour and brown pork chops.
Drain off all grease.
Return to skillet. Pour can of soup mixed with 1/2 cup water over chops. Put onions and green peppers on top of pork chops.
Simmer about 30 minutes, covered.
Salt and pepper may be used, if desired.

title: frances wright's lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, corn meal, lemon juice, butter and egg yolks.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Beat egg whites stiff; fold into first mixture. Pour into rich pie crust; bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until top browns.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer, until pie sets.
Can be stored at room temperature, covered with plastic wrap, or refrigerated.

title: liverwurst spread
directions: Whip cottage cheese to creamy.
Combine liverwurst, cottage cheese, mayonnaise, relish, onion, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Chill until served.
Makes 1 1/4 cups of spread.
Serve on crackers and/or party rye bread.

title: okra patties
directions: Combine okra, onions, salt, pepper, water and egg and mix well.

In another bowl, combine flour, cornmeal and baking powder. Add to okra mixture. Form into patties about the size of silver dollars and fry in just enough shortening to keep from sticking. You may use part squash and potatoes with the okra.

title: german potato salad("hessische art")
directions: Wash and boil potatoes, then peel; cut in slices and put in bowl.
Peel and dice onion; add to potatoes.
Cube and fry bacon; when brown, add 2 bouillon cubes and 1/2 cup water.
Bring to boil.
Pour over potatoes; mix and add vinegar, spices and mayonnaise.
Mix everything under; chill for at least 2 hours.

title: carole's shrimp
directions: Sprinkle meat with meat tenderizer, garlic salt, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Marinate at room temperature for 4 hours. Grill or broil 5 minutes on each side for rare.

title: saucy steak skillet
directions: Pound meat.
Roll in flour and brown in skillet with oil.
Add onion and bell pepper and cook.
Add enough water to potato liquid to measure 1 cup.
Mix liquid, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper and pour over meat mixture.
Add potatoes, beans and pimentos to skillet.
Simmer until done.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix crushed wafers, sugar, pecans or walnuts, cocoa powder, honey and bourbon together until well blended.
(Mixture should be moist but not soggy.)
Roll dough by approximate teaspoonfuls into small balls.
Roll balls in additional sugar.
Store balls in tightly covered tins in a cool dry place.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Peel the tomatoes and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Lay one layer of slices in a shallow baking dish.
Melt the butter and blend the crumbs and remaining ingredients into melted butter.
Sprinkle half of this over the tomato slices; add another layer of slices and use remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread dough in 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Blend cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Spread on baked dough.
Add fruit of your choice, arranging in a circle, beginning at the center and working out.
Bananas, kiwi, blueberries, strawberries, peaches or apples work well.
Dip fresh fruit in lemon juice to keep from turning brown.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well.
Use 2 teaspoons of mix per cup of water.
Good hot or cold.

title: zippy chili con carne
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer for 1 hour.
Add extra water, if needed.

title: cheese fingers
directions: Freeze bread.
Work with 2 slices at a time, keeping remainder in freezer.
Cut off crust and cut into 4 strips.
Dip each in butter and then coat with cornflakes and Parmesan cheese mixture. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° until browned.
The only difficult part is cooking long enough to be crisp without burning.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown beef in hot oil; add garlic and cook until yellow.
Add soy sauce, salt and 1/4 cup water; cook 45 minutes.
Add vegetables; cook 10 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch blended with 1 cup water.
Add tomatoes and cook 5 minutes.
Serve over hot fluffy rice.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend sugar, milk, cocoa and oleo in saucepan.
Boil this mixture for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir mixture and drop by spoonfuls onto tinfoil.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Slice
onions
and
tomatoes
about
1/2-inch thick and place in
layers in a greased casserole with potatoes, celery and carrots.
Sprinkle
each
layer
with
salt,
pepper
and paprika; add fat (this could be 4 strips of bacon), cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: norwegian butter cookies
directions: Melt butter and cool to lukewarm.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add beaten egg, vanilla and dry ingredients, sifted together.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.

title: sugar drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, mixing well.
Stir in milk. Combine dry ingredients and mix in.
Drop mixture from spoon onto cookie sheets; spread with spatula.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until nicely brown.
Remove from sheet immediately and cool on wax paper.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Blend lemonade, Cool Whip and condensed milk together.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Wash chops; season with herbs and spices.
Dip into eggs; roll into crumbs. Place into greased baking dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 400°.
Turn once at halfway point.

title: snow peas and cashew salad
directions: Wash and prepare snow peas (I break the large ones in two). Dice onions.
Prepare flowers of broccoli.
Blend.
Store in fridge.

title: herbed chicken casserole
directions: Season chicken, then brown in butter.
Remove from pan.
Add soup and wine to drippings.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over chicken in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes, then serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients above and simmer until thickened.
In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer with cooked noodles and cheese, alternately.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach smash
directions: Remove pits from peaches and cut into chunks.
Place all ingredients in blender; blend until desired consistency.
Enjoy!

title: orange roughy and vegetables
directions: Spray an 8-inch baking dish with Pam.
Layer onions, carrots and celery in bottom of dish.
Mix tomato sauce, mustard, oregano, garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour 1/2 of sauce in separate bowl.
Add water to remaining sauce and pour over vegetables.
Lay fish over vegetables and sauce.
Pour sauce in separate bowl over fish fillets.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken with walnuts
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2 inch cubes.
Add salt, egg white and cornstarch.
Mix thoroughly by hand.
Heat oil to 400° on wok. Deep fry chicken 2 minutes; remove and drain.
In same oil at 325°, deep fry walnuts in strainer until golden brown; set aside.
Drain oil from wok.
Reheat 2 tablespoons oil in wok to 350°.
Stir-fry red and green peppers 1 minute.
Remove.
Reheat 2 tablespoons oil in wok to 300°.
Add bean sauce, stir 3 minutes.
Add sugar, stir 1 minute, then add stock and sherry.
Stir until dark brown.
Turn up heat to 425°.
Pour in chicken and peppers.
Stir-fry quickly 1 minute.
Remove to platter.
Sprinkle fried walnuts over chicken and serve.

title: spanish string beans
directions: Cut green beans into 1-inch pieces; cook in saucepan, covered, in small amount of boiling salted water until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.

title: killer nachos
directions: Place chips on plate.
Shred cheeses on top.
Place in microwave on Medium-high setting for 1 minute.
Remove and add remaining ingredients to taste.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer ingredients in order.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli until tender.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Cook onion, soup and butter until onion is tender.
Pour rice into casserole dish; top with broccoli and soup mix.
Top with Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Fill baked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: edmunds' family welsh cakes
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in cold butter slices, then squish by hand to mix until fluffy.
In separate bowl, beat egg and milk together.
Stir into flour mixture, forming a sort of pastry dough.
Roll dough into log and cut into 20 slices.
Heat electric skillet to 340° ("pancake").
Cook each slice 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar after first turn on griddle.
Use no oil.
Makes 20 cakes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and pumpkin and beat 2 to 3 minutes until well blended.
Add chocolate chips and walnuts. Bake in ungreased pan at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, carrots and green peppers in butter. Add mushroom soup and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese and corn scallop
directions: Combine corn, celery, carrots, onion, crumbs, eggs, butter, milk, hot pepper sauce and salt, mixing well.
Pour corn mixture into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake until golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in pan over low heat; cool.
Add sugar, molasses and eggs; beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, spices and salt; add to mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: carrot salad
directions: Bring the ingredients to a boil except for the carrots, onion and green pepper.
Cool and pour over carrots, onion and green pepper and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: tortiere
directions: Brown the onions until glassy, then add the ground meat (beef and pork) until fully cooked.
Season with the celery salt and poultry seasoning.
Pour off excess grease from pan.
Add the crushed saltines and mix together, adding the water bit by bit to moisten the crackers and melt them into the meat.
Place the bottom crust into a 9-inch pie plate and pour in the cooked meat mixture.
Cover with the top crust.
Brush with egg white if desired for a browner crust.
Bake in a 375° oven for approximately 20 to 30 minutes, depending on how brown you prefer your crust.
Serve with ketchup on the side.
Tortiere is traditionally served during the winter holidays, and is an absolute "must" on Christmas Eve and on New Year's Eve.
Joyeaux Noel!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all the ingredients together until well blended.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Beat milk, vanilla, margarine and cream cheese until smooth. Slowly add sugar until mixed.
Put on already cooled cake.

title: apple or blueberry crisp
directions: Spread in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: tomato mushroom soup
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in butter.
Add remaining ingredients, except bacon.
Simmer on low heat until hot.
Do not boil.
Ladle into bowls.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Serve with crusty rolls.
Enjoy.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Grease baking dish and put in rhubarb and water.
Mix oats, sugar, cinnamon, flour and butter until crumbles.
Spread over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: aunt maude's five star blueberry muffins
directions: In small bowl, stir
together
1 3/4 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream
margarine
and
sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Add milk mixture to flour mixture, stirring just
until
dry
ingredients
are moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Toss
berries with remaining 1 tablespoon flour; fold into
batter.
Spoon
into 12 greased muffin cups.
Bake in preheated 425°
oven 25 minutes or until evenly golden brown.

title: mom's garlic dill pickles
directions: Sterilize the jars by boiling 20 minutes. Wash cucumbers (2 to 4-inches long) and pack into jars tightly. Add 2 heads dill and 1 clove peeled garlic to each jar.
Combine vinegar, salt and water; heat to boiling. Pour over pickles. Add to top of filled jars, 1 teaspoon alum. Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes. Remove jars from canner and let cool.
Makes 7 quarts.

title: key lime pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add egg yolks; beat.
Add lime juice; beat.
Add milk; beat.
Pour into a graham cracker crust and chill.
Will set better if baked in oven approximately 5 minutes at 350°.

title: 100 year old cookies
directions: Cream
sugar and shortening;
add eggs, milk and vanilla. Stir
in
dry
ingredients	and mix well.
Chill dough in spring house
for 30 minutes.
Bake in hot oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut butter in dry ingredients with fork or pie blender.
Beat egg and milk together.
Dust blueberries with 1 tablespoon flour.
Add egg and milk to dry ingredients; fold in blueberries.
Grease and flour bread pan.
Pour into bread pan and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Take out of pan and cook on rack.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, salt and milk; bring to a boil.
Boil slowly for 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Add 1 box powdered sugar.
May add a little water or coffee to make it spread easier.

title: crab spread
directions: Cream mayonnaise and cheese well.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Serve with bagelettes, crackers.

title: chewy bars
directions: Combine corn syrup and sugar in medium saucepan and bring to a slow boil.
Add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Pour over cereal and mix until completely coated.
Press cereal mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: shrimp 'n chicken gumbo
directions: Cook chicken and water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes or until chicken is done. Remove chicken from broth; set aside to cool. Strain broth, if desired, and transfer to a large container; set aside. Bone and chop chicken; set aside.

title: ritz cracker ice cream dessert
directions: Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan; bake 5 minutes in 250° oven.
Cool completely.

title: real fudge icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except vanilla.
Boil fast for 2 minutes from boiling point.
Add vanilla.
Beat for 5 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart microwave glass casserole, stir together sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes.
Mixture should come to a vigorous boil in all areas and boil about 1 minute and 15 seconds.

title: spanish meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, 1/3 cup of sauce and remaining ingredients.
Spread in ungreased loaf pan.
Spread remaining sauce over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Measure into blender.
Cover; mix until thick and smooth.

title: special baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and onion together until bacon is crisp and onion is soft.
Place all beans into large baking dish; mix well.
Add sugar, garlic and bacon-onion mixture.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on a serving dish (10 to 12-inch dish). Spread shrimp on cream cheese.
Cover with cocktail sauce and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese, then green onions.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with crushed cornflakes and slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Cover bottom of 1 1/2-quart baking dish with whole vanilla wafers.
Pour Eagle Brand milk into a mixing bowl.
Add lemon juice, stirring until thickened.
Add fruit cocktail, bananas and nuts.
Pour on the wafers.
Cover with Dream Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Cut into squares.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in a bowl with a wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in lemon peel and juice. Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the whipped topping.
Spread evenly in bottom of the crust.
Press strawberry halves into cream cheese layer, reserving several for garnish, if desired.
Pour 2 cups milk into bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with a wire whisk 1 minute or until thickened.
Gently stir in 1 cup of the whipped topping.
Spoon over strawberries in the crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and reserved strawberry halves.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt cheese in saucepan.
Add the sour cream and mayonnaise. Stir to mix well.
Pour over new potatoes, asparagus, broccoli or boiled small onions.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Mix salad dressing and orange juice in small bowl.
Pour over salad; toss lightly.
Top with egg quarters and croutons.

title: applesauce spice muffins with oatmeal
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add oatmeal and raisins.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with applesauce to creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes one dozen.
Lightly oil muffin pan with cooking oil.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Blend butter, margarine, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Fold in oats, flour and salt, sifted together.
Shape into balls, then crescents.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In blender, mix zucchini, oil, eggs and vanilla. In mixing bowl, mix sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder. Add blender mixture and mix well.
Add nuts, if desired. Pour into 2 well greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes.
Drain and place 1/2 in a greased 10 x 14-inch baking dish.
Make a white sauce by melting margarine and adding flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and stir until boiling and thickened.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Pour 1/2 over potatoes in baking dish, add a layer of potatoes and the remainder of the sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until browned.

title: decorator frosting
directions: Blend together Crisco and sugar.
Slowly add water to reach the consistency you want.
Add the almond last.
If you plan to use liquid food coloring, adjust the amount of water you add to avoid a too thin frosting.

title: onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex pan.
Peel and slice onions and separate into rings. Put into a medium sized saucepan and cover with hot water.
Boil 1 minute.
Drain well. Spread onions evenly in the 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with the parsley.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice as package directions.
Add all other ingredients and stir until blended.
Add rice to mixture.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a 2-quart glass dish.
Combine flour, oats, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender or microwave 14 minutes until tender.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and slice in round slices.
Layer potatoes in a casserole dish.
Layer pork chops.
Add Campbell's Cheddar cheese soup (undiluted).

Cover and bake in a 350° oven for one hour. (Sometimes the potatoes are too firm, so if you choose, you can boil the whole potatoes for a few minutes and then slice them after they cool, as you would for diced potato salad.)

title: salmon casserole
directions: Lutefisk is referred to by many, even Norwegians, as "the piece of Cod which passeth all understanding".

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes for 15 minutes.
Peel and cut into lengthwise sections.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Combine sugar, salt, butter and water in a saucepan.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour syrup over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes. Baste occasionally with syrup mixture as desired.

title: el dorado beef casserole
directions: Cook beef in a cold skillet on medium-high heat.
Saute in its own fat until crumbly and pink color is gone.
Drain off excess fat.
Add onion, garlic salt, tomato sauce and olives to beef. Combine sour cream, cottage cheese and chilies.
Crush tortilla chips slightly.
Place half the chips on bottom of a well-greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add half the meat mixture, cover with half the sour cream mixture and sprinkle with half the grated cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until bubbly.

title: best chicken dressing
directions: Mix crumbs with chicken broth and cream of chicken soup; let stand for a few minutes.
Add chopped celery, onions and bell pepper.
Add sage, salt, sugar, pepper, boiled eggs and butter. Pour into greased pan and bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out 1 loaf of defrosted dough to 10 x 14-inch size.
Cook sausage with onion; drain.
Sprinkle dough with oregano and garlic powder.
Spread sausage mixture on top.
Place pepperoni slices next to each other, covering dough, then do the same with the Provolone cheese.
Lightly sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
(I sprinkle Parmesan cheese on the dough before spreading the sausage mixture.)
Roll like a jelly roll, turning ends under to seal and pinching seams.
Brush with egg whites right before placing in oven (gives a finished look).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onions in frying pan and brown ground beef; season with spices.
Mix onions, ground beef and 1/2 cheese in a bowl.
Dip tortillas in warm oil, just long enough to coat sides (soften the tortillas) and fill with one to two spoonfuls of meat mixture.
Roll closed and place in 13 x 9-inch baking pan with seam down.
Mix mushroom sauce and enchilada sauce; pour over rolled tortillas.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Allow to cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Add only 1 cup of the flour, add baking soda.
Beat well.
Stir in remaining 2 1/4 cups of flour, grated zucchini, vanilla and nuts.
Pour mixture into regular sized greased bread loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter casserole
dish.
Crumble
1/2 of crackers.
Cut 1/2 margarine stick
into small pieces and place over crumbled crackers. Layer
chicken.
Mix
soups
and sour cream together and pour over ingredients.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs and dot with remaining margarine. Cook in oven at 350° to 375° until brown and bubbly.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with raw vegetables.
If 16 ounces of sour cream is used, triple all other ingredients.

title: bread machine anise bread
directions: Put ingredients in bread machine in order given.
Select "sweet bread" setting.
Adjust baking control to medium.
Start machine.
Remove when done.
After bread has cooled, top with glaze and colored sprinkles.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Test for doneness as you would a cake.
Sprinkle with small package of shredded Mozzarella cheese until melted.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown meat with onion and salt, pepper and garlic to taste. Spray Pam on bottom of baking dish.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Cook sugar and Karo over low heat until sugar melts and mixture starts to bubble.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter. Add 6 cups of Rice Krispies; mix well.
Press mixture into buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips over low heat.
Spread over Krispies.
Cool and serve.

title: hobo pie
directions: Boil potatoes; drain, then mash.
Cook carrots.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Mix carrots with ground beef and onions. Pour mixture in a casserole dish.
Pour mashed potatoes over mixture and seal edges completely.
Place cheese over top and bake at 325° until brown.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, whisk together the oil, chili powder, oregano and cumin to blend well.
Pulverize the tortilla chips in a food processor.
Pour into a shallow bowl.
Dip the chicken in the seasoned oil, then coat in the ground chips. Set on foil-lined baking sheet and bake for 45 minutes until browned and crisp outside and tender inside.
Serve hot.

title: bacon cream cheese roll-ups
directions: With an electric mixer, whip cream cheese and cream together. Spread cream cheese on bread slices and cut in half, then cut each half into three pieces.
Also, cut bacon into 2 1/2 to 3-inch strips.
Roll up halves, with filling on the inside.
Wrap with a slice of bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
These can be frozen at this point.
Bake until brown on one side; turn and brown on the other side.
Bake at 300° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: madonna salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Boil 2 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese (room temperature) and baby food.
Fold in Jell-O mixture and Cool Whip. Chill.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cut biscuits into thirds.
Wrap dough around cheese cubes. Fry for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain on towel.
Makes 30.

title: picante sauce
directions: Cook on top of the stove 1 1/2 hours.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: cambric tea
directions: Put sugar in a cup.
Add cream and let stand a minute to melt sugar.
Fill cup with boiling water.
Yields 3/4 cup.

title: hamburger upside-down bake
directions: Brown meat and next 4 ingredients in 10-inch skillet.
Fry until brown.
Push mixture evenly around skillet, forming ring. Spread undrained corn in center.
Mix corn bread batter and pour evenly over meat and corn.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 20 to 25 minutes or until corn bread is done.
Remove from oven; let stand 5 minutes.
Turn upside-down on hot serving plate.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain canned beans.
Mix all ingredients and let set in the refrigerator overnight.

title: fruit slush punch
directions: Boil water and sugar; cool.
Add next 4 ingredients; mix well. Freeze in a covered flat container.
When needed for serving, let set until slightly softened, 1 to 2 hours.
Scrape frozen mixture into punch bowl to form slush.
Add 7-Up and lemon juice; serve.

title: never fail sweet rye bread
directions: Scald and cool molasses, syrup, sugar, milk and shortening. Then add yeast, dissolved in warm water and rye flour.
Add white flour to make a stiff dough.
Place in greased bowl, cover with damp cloth.
Let rise until double, about 3 hours.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Combine chicken cubes, soups, sour cream and mushrooms.
Pour into slightly greased casserole dish.
Cover with dressing (use in dry form.)
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: In saucepan mix ingredients with pineapple juice and cook until thick.
Add more cornstarch if needed.
Add meatballs, pineapple and green pepper.
Cook until heated through.

title: chicken on sunday
directions: Combine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken pieces on top. Sprinkle with 1 envelope onion soup mix.
Seal tightly with foil. Bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: frozen salad
directions: Soak marshmallows and pineapple overnight.
Mix salad dressing and soft cream cheese.
Next mix everything together.
Freeze. Serve as desired.

title: cherry-nut bread
directions: In mixing bowl, thoroughly stir together flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, cream together sugar, butter or margarine, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately to creamed mixture.
Beat just until blended after each addition.
Fold in nuts and cherries. Bake in greased, 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan; cool.
If desired, glaze with confectioners icing.

title: successful meringue
directions: Moisten the cornstarch in water.
Stir in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Cook until thick and clear, then cool.
Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Add salt and sugar.
Beat in the cooled cornstarch.
Brown at 325°.

title: hot deviled clam snack
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper; blend.
Drain clams and add quantity of milk to juice to make one cup.
Add liquid to flour mixture gradually, until thick. Add remaining ingredients except for bread crumbs.
Place in shallow glass pie plate.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake until brown at 350° or about 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in frypan and add required amount of water as seasoned stuffing package directions.
Add seasoned stuffing to frypan and mix.
Reserve 1/4 cup of stuffing mixture for final topping.
Combine cooked broccoli, stuffing mixture and remaining ingredients.
Place in a casserole dish and top with reserved stuffing.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: apple pie brownie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Stir in flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and baking soda (that has been dissolved in 2 tablespoons hot water).
Fold in apples and nuts. Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve with Caramel Sauce.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in heavy saucepan over low heat until thicker and syrupy. Will keep in refrigerator 1 week. Makes 1 1/2 cups of sauce.

title: mrs. meadows chocolate chip cookie(mrs. fields ... almost)
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift baking soda, baking powder and flour.
Add dry mixture to butter mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, milk chocolate bars and chocolate chips.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet mustard dip
directions: Whip all ingredients together until blended.

title: apache cheese bread dip
directions: Slice top off French bread; scoop out center of bread and discard.
Replace top and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Remove top from bread and place mixture inside loaf.
Replace the top and bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh fruit sundaes
directions: Combine fruit in medium bowl; spoon into 4 serving dishes. Top with yogurt; sprinkle with trail mix. Makes 4 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger with onions and peppers.
Pour off excess drippings.
Add spaghetti sauce, sugar, mushrooms, Philadelphia cream cheese and cottage cheese.
Bring to a boil and simmer.

title: sara's wintertime hot chocolate
directions: Combine ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
For each serving, 1/3 c. mix into mug and add boiling water.

title: turkey twist casserole
directions: In skillet, heat olive oil and cook broccoli and carrots with basil and garlic powder until tender, stirring often.
Stir in soup, milk and cheese.
Add macaroni and turkey.
Heat through, stirring often.
Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drained.
Add corn, tomato sauce, bell pepper, salt and pepper.
Stir ingredients together for 5 minutes on low heat.
Pour into casserole pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in oven at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: vanilla biscuit tortoni
directions: (Be sure you are using almond macaroons.)
Mash macaroons to crumbs, then add milk, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Whip cream; fold into the macaroon mixture.
Place cupcake liners in cupcake tins; fill with mixture.
Freeze until firm. Sprinkle with slivered almonds and top with maraschino cherry.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and add remaining ingredients.
Place in baking dish and top with Nut Topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin gobs
directions: Beat egg yolks, brown sugar and oil together.
Add the remaining dry ingredients along with the pumpkin and vanilla. Drop on cookie sheet by tablespoon that has been greased lightly. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Cream together margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian sausage spaghetti(not the kind of sausage used for gravy)
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Cook sausage in skillet; careful not to brown too heavily.
Remove and set aside.
In large pan, cook tomato juice or sauce.
May want to use canned.
Add peppers, mushrooms, onion and season to your taste.
(I like to use garlic, dab of sugar and Italian seasoning.)
Toss spaghetti.
Place in long serving container and arrange sausage on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: broccoli surprise a la sandy
directions: Combine and pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart dish.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 370° for 10 minutes or until light brown in color.
Dough may be refrigerated overnight.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well, fold in blueberries.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour in a tube or Bundt pan, which has been greased and floured.

title: orange glazed chicken
directions: For glaze, combine first 3 ingredients in a small bowl. Lightly flatten chicken breasts to uniform thickness.
In a large skillet, melt margarine.
Add chicken.
Brown both sides.
Pour glaze over chicken; simmer covered for about 10 minutes, then uncover and simmer, basting occasionally until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Contains 219 calories and 4 g fat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook milk, sugar, Karo, salt, butter and dates until it will form a soft ball or 1 mark above soft on candy thermometer. Remove from heat; add nuts and vanilla.
Beat until creamy and stiff.
Divide into two pieces on damp thin cloths.
Roll out rolls.
When cool, remove from cloth and wrap in foil.
Slice in thin pieces.

title: pickles
directions: Wrap turmeric, cloves and mustard seeds in cloth. Wash cucumber and slice as thin as possible.
Chop onions and peppers. Combine the three with salt and let stand for 3 hours, then drain. Combine vinegar, sugar and spices in a large kettle. Bring to a boil and add cucumber mixture
and heat to a boil. Pack and seal in jars.

title: rump roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with garlic salt or cut and insert garlic.
Put roast in covered pan. Place in oven at 450° for 30 minutes. Leave in oven, without opening, all day or night.

title: deviled eggs with ham
directions: Hard boil eggs for 12 minutes.
Cool eggs for 30 minutes.
Cut eggs in half; set aside whites.
Mix all remaining ingredients together with egg yolks.
Fill egg whites and garnish with a little chopped ham.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray a Bundt pan with Pam.
Take 2 cans of biscuits and cut into quarters.
Stack them in the pan.
Melt butter, cinnamon and brown sugar and pour half of mixture over the biscuits.
Take remaining 2 cans of biscuits and liquid mixture and do the same. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: short cut shortcake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a fork to moisten and then beat vigorously for about 45 seconds.
Spread dough in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan, pulling up the edges slightly.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool for about 5 minutes. Split into 2 layers with serrated knife and fill with the fresh fruit of your choice.

title: no bake butterballs
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add sugar.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well. Shape into small balls. Roll in nuts or coconut, if desired.
Store in refrigerator. Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken cacciatore(4 servings)
directions: Flour chicken pieces.
Heat frypan to 340°.
Add chicken and lightly brown.
Remove chicken.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook about 3 minutes.
Add chicken and all ingredients except parsley.
Cover.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook 30 minutes until chicken is tender.
Turn chicken occasionally and add parsley and serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crumble Oreos in blender.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remainder in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour melted butter over Oreos.
Shape into crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and half of Cool Whip.
Layer on top of crust.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground meat; drain excess grease. Add onion and stir-fry until onion begins to turn clear. Add chopped cabbage, and raw rice; pour tomato sauce on top. Season with salt, pepper, and Tony's seasoning. Add enough water to cook until cabbage is done.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook the chicken by boiling then cut into pieces.
Mix the chicken soup, milk and sour cream into a sauce.
Use a large roasting pan or pyrex 9 x 13 lightly greased.
Roll into a tortilla chicken, chilies, cheese and sauce and place in pan.
Continue with other tortillas saving some sauce, chilies and cheese for the top. Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar, oil and eggs together. Add all other ingredients. Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: On a baking sheet, combine butter, pecans, 1 tablespoon granulated sugar and salt.
Spread in a single layer.
Roast at 350° for 15 minutes.
Stir and roast 15 minutes more.
Cool.

title: mock sour cream dip
directions: Put first 3 ingredients through blender and season to taste. Serve as a vegetable dip.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cut up cabbage 5 minutes.
Layer cream of chicken soup, grated cheese and cabbage.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni and toss with oil.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Cook in crock-pot on low for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except marshmallows.
Take small amount and roll around a marshmallow, then roll ball in crushed corn flakes.
Brown in medium hot oil in skillet; keep turning until golden brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and both sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed ingredients slowly.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Roll out on lightly floured surface and cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° until done, not brown, approximately 8 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread crescent rolls (not cooked). In a skillet, brown sausage and drain off grease. Place on top of rolls in pan. Beat eggs with milk. Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour over sausage. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: company broccoli
directions: Crush crackers.
Melt margarine and add to cracker crumbs. Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Put 1/2 of crumb mixture in bottom. On top of crumbs put 1/2 pound cheese, cubed.
On top of that place cooked broccoli.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, covered.

title: coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage extra fine using chef's knife or grater.
To avoid last minute, toss cabbage with ice cubes.
Hold in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Remove ice and drain.

title: dirty rice
directions: In a baking dish, mix soup, beef consomme and rice, add mushrooms and stir. Lay stick of margarine over top, cover dish. Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in an airtight container. Makes a lot.
To make hot chocolate:
Mix 1/3 cup hot chocolate mix to 1 cup hot water.
Stir well.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Layer chicken in oblong baking dish or crock-pot.
Combine all remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or cook in crock-pot for 3 to 4 hours on high or 8 to 10 hours on low.
Serve over rice.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Flake crabmeat into fine pieces.
Add only enough sour cream to make it easily spreadable (add a little mayonnaise if you get it too thin).
Put in small amount of horseradish, maybe 1 or 2 tablespoons.
Sprinkle with chives.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Remove and add more horseradish or chives or other seasoning, if needed.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all together; put in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: lemon meltaways
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix at low speed 2 to 3 minutes. Shape into two 8 x 1-inch rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and chill 1 to 2 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes.
Cookies will not brown!

title: mother's delight
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk together in double boiler.
When cool, add lemon juice, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Crush graham crackers and put mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan. Put mixture in and cover with remaining graham crackers.
Chill.

title: thumbprints
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except preserves.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed, 2 to 3 minutes.
Shape rounded teaspoonful of dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheets. Make a depression in the center of each cookie with the back of a teaspoon.
Bake 8 minutes. Remove from oven.
Fill centers with preserves.
Continue baking 6 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: vinegar pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, sugar and salt together until particles are the size of peas. Mix egg, water and vinegar in a small bowl. Then add to the flour mixture. Mix until it forms a ball in the bowl. Makes 5 pie shells or 2 double crust pie crust, plus one pie shell. Can be divided and frozen or kept in the refrigerator. Roll on floured surface. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until done. Very good and easy to work with.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix thoroughly.
For additional flavor, add 1/4 cup Hershey's cocoa and 1/4 to 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Mix, then add 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: mexican potato soup
directions: Brown bacon in large pan; drain.
Add the potato cubes and mix.
Add broth, water, tomato sauce, onion and salt.
Bring to a simmer and cook until potatoes are tender.

title: date and nut mini cakes
directions: Mix sugar, chopped nuts and dates together.
Add beaten eggs to the mixture.
Fill mini pan 3/4 full.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
When cool, place in mini paper cups.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion.
Place potatoes in 2-quart baking dish.
Drain peas and carrots and save the juice.
Place peas and carrots over potatoes.
Pour hamburger mixture over potatoes, peas and carrots.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt. Combine soup with liquid from peas and carrots and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt margarine and cheese.
Add sugar, cocoa, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: ice cream cake number 1
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Press 3/4 of mixture on 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze.
Soften 1/2 gallon vanilla ice cream and spread on crust and freeze.
Pour one large can of chocolate syrup on ice cream.
Sprinkle Rice Chex mixture on top and freeze.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In large saucepan, bring sugar, oleo and milk to boil over medium heat.
Stirring continually, cook until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water.
Remove pan from heat and add Reese's Pieces, marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Heat milk in a double boiler to scalding point.
Mix together sugar, flour and salt.
Add gradually to the hot milk.
Stir until mixture is smooth and thick.
Cover and cook over water 15 minutes.
Pour mixture over well beaten egg yolks; return mixture to double boiler and cook 2 minutes.
Cool mixture and stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar slowly.
Add vanilla.
Spread on top of pie and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 300° until brown.

title: barbecue pork marinade
directions: Into the marinating container, add the bottle of soy, water, onion and garlic.
Add the meat.
Marinate for 2 to 3 hours. Throw on barbecue and baste occasionally.

title: refrigerator biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water.
Heat second cup of water and dissolve Crisco in it, then let it cool.
Beat eggs and add sugar and salt to eggs, then mix with other liquids and gradually add flour.
Mix well; put in greased bowl and cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip biscuits in melted butter; let rise.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spread hash browns in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Pour 1/2 of melted oleo on top.
Sprinkle chopped onion over the top.
Heat cheese, sour cream and soup.
Pour over potatoes in casserole dish.
Mix crushed corn flakes and oleo and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: johnny's navy dressing
directions: Mix equal parts of vinegar, sugar, oil and ketchup.
Shake well and serve over your salad.
To use this recipe for slaw, delete ketchup.

title: diana's yeast bread
directions: Scald milk and add butter.
Set aside to cool.
In a large bowl, mix first three ingredients.
Let stand five minutes.
When milk mixture is cooled to lukewarm, add to yeast.
Add salt and 3 cups of flour.
Beat well.
Add enough more flour to make soft dough.
Place remaining flour on board.
Turn out dough on floured board and knead.
Place dough in a large greased bowl.
Grease top of dough.
Let raise until double.
Punch down.
Cut dough into halves, round ends, cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Put into greased bread pans.
Let raise until double.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes longer.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let stand.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate for 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave potatoes au gratin
directions: Microwave butter for 45 seconds or until melted.
Layer 1/3 of potatoes and 1/3 of onion on bottom of 3-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle lightly with salt, pepper and paprika.
Sprinkle 1/3 of the cheeses; drizzle with 1/3 of the butter.
Repeat layers until all ingredients used.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 16 minutes, rotating 1/2 turn after 8 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and rinse potatoes; peel skin if too tough.
Cut potatoes into slices but not all the way through.
(Use the handle of a wooden spoon as guide to prevent knife from cutting all the way through.)
Put potatoes in baking dish.
Fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs. Bake potatoes at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned or until the cheese is melted and the potatoes stick done with a fork.

title: bread pudding
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, milk, sugar, cinnamon and vanilla together; place dry bread cubes in 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish.
Sprinkle with raisins or fruit over the bread.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Prepare baking pan as for regular cornbread. Pour half of mixture into pan.
Put cheese on this.
Add remainder of mixture.
Top with rest of cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: finger lickin' wings
directions: Separate chicken wings	into
pieces.
(Do
not
use tips.) Marinate remaining	pieces	at
least
3 hours or overnight. Place wings
on foil-covered sheet, making sure pieces do not touch.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cookie apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine apples, sugar, flour, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, allspice and lemon juice; toss to coat apples well.
Spoon into ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Use half of dough; drop by scant teaspoons evenly over apples.
(Wrap remaining cookie dough and refrigerate for later use.)

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Mix cooked, drained macaroni and other ingredients together. Pour into buttered casserole.
Cover top with cracker crumbs; sprinkle with melted butter and cook at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal herb loaf
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Saute onion in oil.
Add salt, basil and oregano.
Blend all ingredients together and place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 60 minute or until done.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Melt chocolate and butter on very low heat. Pour into a small bowl and mix in powdered sugar, milk, egg whites and vanilla. Place bowl in a larger bowl of ice and beat on low speed until spreading consistency. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix sliced bananas with lemon juice.
Mix other ingredients together.
Blend in bananas.
Mix in can of peach pie filling. Cool until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, water and eggs until smooth.
Add 1/2 jar of peanut butter.
Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans.
Pour mixture into pans and cook for 35 to 40 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening to flour.
Add water; knead 10 minutes.
Roll 1/8 inch thick.
Cut into squares.
Deep fry.

title: easy beer bread
directions: Stir together the flour and sugar.
Add beer and mix with fork until combined (do not overmix).
Turn batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: Beat together oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, salt and baking soda together, then add to sugar mixture.
Add peaches, nuts and vanilla.
Mix together.
Bake at 325° for one hour or until done.

title: chocolate lover's chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup chocolate pieces in mixing bowl; mix until well blended (about 4 minutes at medium speed).
Fold in 1/2 cup chocolate pieces.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 12 cup Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
(Note: If Bundt pan is porcelain coated and Teflon lined, reduce temperature to 325°.)
Cool 10 minutes before removing to rack to cool completely.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook celery and onions in skillet until done, add meat and brown.
Drain grease off this and add to soup, rice and salt in a casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese. Bake in oven at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: fudge no bake cookies
directions: In saucepan, add the oleo, sugar and milk. Bring to a rolling boil and have ready the oatmeal, cocoa and nuts. Add the vanilla to milk mixture when you take it off of the stove. Drop cookies on a greased cookie sheet. Let stand for a few minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together the first 9 ingredients; set aside.
Melt over double boiler the Eagle Brand milk, chocolate chips, vanilla, oleo and salt.
Add nuts, if desired.
Spread 2/3 of first mixture on greased jelly roll pan.
Spread chocolate mixture over this.
Dot with remaining first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garden casserole
directions: *These vegies can be canned.

title: seafood bisque pronto
directions: Combine pea and tomato soups with cream in saucepan; heat 15 minutes, stirring often.
(Do not boil.)
Add crab meat or shrimp; simmer 10 minutes.
(Do not boil.)
Remove from heat; stir in brown sugar and rum.
Serve in consomme cups; garnish with chives.

title: cake
directions: Beat the stuf and cook.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until clean.
Add soup, soy sauce and rice.
Mix well.
Add Cheez Whiz and let melt; stir well.
Pour into casserole; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pita toast
directions: Cream together first 6 ingredients.
Chill margarine mixture at least 1 hour (overnight is best).
Halve 6 pita rounds and separate each half into 2 pieces.
Spread the inside of each piece with some of the margarine mixture.
Arrange bread on a baking sheet in one layer.
Bake it in top third of oven at 450° (preheated) for 5 minutes or until lightly browned and crisp.
Great with soups and pasta.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Combine spaghetti sauce and tomatoes in crock-pot (high heat). Add garlic powder and oregano.

title: blueberry soup
directions: Rinse the blueberries and remove any stems, leaves or green berries.
Put the berries in a kettle and add the water, cloves and cinnamon stick.
Set over moderate heat and bring to a boil.
Stir in honey; reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, until berries are very tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool to room temperature.
Force the soup through a strainer or through the medium blade of a food mill.
Stir in lemon juice, creme de cassis and vinegar.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 6 hours.
Serve in chilled bowls, garnished with a few whole blueberries, a dollop of plain yogurt and a sprinkle of grated orange rind.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Saute onions and bell pepper in butter.
Add all ingredients together, except cracker crumbs mashed in butter.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover with cheese, then sprinkle with crackers that have been mashed in butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: cream tacos
directions: Melt in saucepan the cheese, tomatoes and chilies, milk, onion and soup.
Brown in skillet, beef, salt and chili powder.
Heat until soft the tortillas.
Line a large dish with 1/2 of the tortillas, 1/2 of meat mixture, 1/2 of cheese mixture, rest of tortillas on top, then rest of beef and cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cajun style drumsticks
directions: Place chicken in a shallow dish; pour buttermilk over top. Cover and chill for 8 hours.
Place butter in a shallow dish; set aside.
Combine flour, cornmeal and seasonings in a plastic bag. Drain chicken; roll in butter and place in bag, 1 or 2 pieces at a time.
Close bag securely and shake until well coated.
Arrange chicken on a rack placed over a roasting pan; drizzle with any remaining butter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn chicken; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 or 35 minutes or until done. Yield:
4 servings.

title: chicken and cabbage
directions: Cooking Time: 1 hour.

title: rice pudding
directions: Wash rice.
Cook rice with a little water.
Before water evaporates, add warm milk and stir.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Add sugar and vanilla and cook another 15 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add beaten egg, stirring constantly while adding egg so that egg does not cook.
Pour into individual serving dishes or large bowl and refrigerate.
Serve cold.
(If a little thick, add some cold milk to serving and stir.)

title: brownies
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add chocolate syrup, flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into an ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: risotto (italian rice)
directions: Chop liver and gizzards.
Cook all the vegetables in the butter and oil.
Cook the meat with it.
Put the tomato paste with this.
Add small amount of broth to sauce and cook slow until well done.
Add the rice and the broth.
When the rice is cooked, add the cheese and serve.

title: spicy chicken wings
directions: Soften honey in warm water.
Mix in other ingredients. Arrange wings in shallow pan and cover with the sauce.
Add enough water to cover the top of the wings.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours, then increase temperature to 375° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: italian macaroni and cheese
directions: In a large pot, heat water and crumbled bouillon cubes.
When boiling, add macaroni.
Cook according to package instructions until just al dente.
Drain well.
Cut ham into small strips. Place a layer of pasta over bottom of a slightly greased pan. Sprinkle with some ham, then continue layering pasta and ham.

title: lentil soup
directions: Soak lentils overnight. Bring them to boil in the same liquid and allow to simmer for 3/4 hour. Add diced potatoes and smoked sausage, if desired and cook until potatoes are done. In skillet, brown the onion and bacon and add flour as thickener. Pour quickly into soup mixture. Add bouillon cubes if desired. Serve when ready.

title: coconut fruit salad supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients. Fold in whipped cream and garnish with shredded coconut.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone when cool.
Reserve broth. Saute in margarine the bell pepper, celery and onions until tender.
Add soup, olives, salt, pepper, 1/2 cup broth and 1/2 cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Bring salted broth to boil. Add water to broth to make enough liquid to cook 2 to 3 cups noodles.
Add to vegetable and chicken mixture.
Pour in lightly greased casserole.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Heat in 350° oven about 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm water.
Melt butter, stir in sugar in large bowl, then add beaten egg.
Add dissolved yeast to creamed mixture, then add flour and stir until well mixed.
Place in an airtight bowl and keep in refrigerator.

title: crustless ham and cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Spray 9-inch pie pan with Baker's Joy. Scatter ham, broccoli and cheese evenly in pan. Whisk remaining ingredients in a bowl until blended. Pour in pan. Bake 40 minutes or until firm.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding mix.
Add sour cream and 1/2 carton of Cool Whip.
Layer bananas, vanilla wafers and pudding mix.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until clear, then add Jell-O and pour over strawberries in pie crust.
Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: lillian's rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, powdered sugar and margarine as for a pie crust.
Press in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch casserole for 1 hour.
Makes 10-12 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Mix cubed cheese into cooked macaroni.
Beat together milk and eggs.
Place macaroni and cheese in a casserole dish.
Pour milk and eggs over the top.
Cover with sliced Longhorn cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Remove foil and bake until slightly brown on top.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Important:
Wear rubber gloves when cleaning hot peppers.

title: beef and cheese ball
directions: In small bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Mix well. Shape into balls.
Makes 10 servings.

title: lobster dip
directions: Chop lobster very fine.
Mash yolks only (reserve whites for salad or other recipe).
Add yolks to lobster.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Serve on crackers or party rye, heated in broiler.

title: meat loaf roll
directions: Drain and squeeze broccoli and spinach.
Mix hamburger, eggs, bread crumbs, catsup, milk, 2 teaspoons salt and pepper.
Pat hamburger mixture into a rectangle (about 12 x 10-inches), on piece of plastic wrap or aluminum foil.
Arrange broccoli on hamburger rectangle to within 1/2-inch of edges; arrange ham on top of broccoli.
Sprinkle shredded Mozzarella on top of ham; sprinkle garlic salt on top of cheese.
Roll up rectangle carefully, beginning at 10-inch side and using the plastic or foil wrap to lift.
Press edges and ends of roll to seal.

title: cake crumb cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla and mix. Stir in pecans.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Mix items in order as given.
Add egg whites last.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: heirloom boston brown bread
directions: Combine well and spoon into 4 well-greased 1 pound tin cans. Let stand for 1 hour.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool and remove from cans.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate (9 or 10-inch).
Blend all ingredients on high for 15 seconds.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix together with mixer.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: garlic and honey barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Put chicken in baking pan, single layer; pour sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning once.
May add extra sauce when you turn.

title: pizza treats
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger and drain.
Cut up and melt Velveeta cheese in meat mixture.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, oregano and garlic salt.
Place on party rye bread and bake 6 minutes at 300°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown lean beef.
Drain.
Cook egg noodles and drain.
Drain corn and tomatoes.
Chop onion and bell pepper.
Place all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put into lightly oiled casserole and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Good with a tossed salad and garlic bread sticks.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts and dates.
Beat eggs and add slowly to mixture.
Form into little balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lime jello with apricots salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add 7-Up and cold water. Stuff apricots with cream cheese and pecans.
Place in jello mold and pour jello over stuffed apricots.
Place in refrigerator and let set.

title: chocolate sour cream raisin cake
directions: Make and bake cake
mix as directed in a 9 x 13 pan. Combine the brown sugar, cornstarch, eggs, nuts, white sugar, sour cream, raisins and vanilla in a double boiler and cook until thick.
Spread over cake.
Cool.
Mix together the margarine, powdered sugar, hot water, chocolate and vanilla until smooth and pour over cake.

title: chunky applesauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a large saucepan. Cover and cook over low to medium heat for 45 to 60 minutes or until apples are tender.
Remove from heat and mash apples. Serve warm or cold.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9 X 13 cake pan; set aside.
Cream together butter, oil, sugar, salt, eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Stir together the remaining dry ingredients.
Add to liquid, mixing well.
Add grated zucchini, mixing well.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake 40-45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Peel and cut carrots into 1-inch wounds.
Combine with 1 cup of water.
Cover and simmer until barely done, about 20 minutes. Dissolve the cornstarch in the remaining 1/4 cup water and add to the carrots, along with the honey, salt and ginger.
Stir over low heat until mixture thickens.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mincemeat
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Cook over very low heat for 45 minutes. Fill into jars. Seal while hot.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add all dry ingredients.
Fold in drained pineapple, carrots and nuts.
Pour mixture into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: aunt dell's peanut clusters
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk.
Boil 6 minutes, counting from time bubbling begins.
Add butter, nuts and vanilla.
Stir just enough to mix in nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: easy poached chicken
directions: Preheat 4-quart roaster oven to 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy pickin' chicken pie(makes 6 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease shallow 2-quart casserole. Spread chicken and vegetables evenly in bottom of greased dish. In medium bowl, combine soup, broth and pepper; mix well. Pour evenly over chicken mixture. In another medium bowl, combine flour, milk and butter. Stir until smooth. Pour over chicken mixture in casserole. Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan mix soup, mayonnaise and pepper with chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until it starts to bubble.

title: oven pancakes
directions: Beat milk, eggs, vanilla and flour well.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan and pour batter over melted butter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.
Serve with syrup or honey.

title: peanut butter no egg cookies
directions: Mix everything but flour.
Add flour.
Cook 8 minutes at 350° on greased cookie sheet.
Makes 30.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles by directions.
