Place into buttered casserole. Break up tuna over noodles.
Mix soup and milk together; pour over.
Spread cheese on top and sprinkle pepper.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook ground beef in margarine and onion powder until brown. Mix in broth, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Spread mashed potatoes over meat mixture, sealing to edge of pan.
Run a fork over potatoes for rippled surface.
Put in a preheated 425° oven for about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
With a fork put small holes in cake.
Cover with glaze.

title: sumptious crab mold
directions: Heat undiluted soup with 2 tablespoons water and gelatine.
Add cream cheese, mayonnaise, celery, onions and crabmeat.
Mix and mold overnight.

title: bishop asbury pound cake
directions: Cream
together
softened butter and sugar, using heavy duty mixer.
Add
eggs,	one
at
a
time
with mixer running continuously
at
medium
speed.
Add lemon juice and vanilla. Add sifted
flour,
a	little bit at a time.
Mix thoroughly. Bake in	a
greased
and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until straw test shows it's done.
Cool on rack before taking out of pan.

title: sunday fried chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken and oil.
Place about 1 cup mixture in bag.
Shake a few pieces of chicken at a time to coat well.
Put 1/4-inch oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Brown chicken on all sides, remove and put in large shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Blend flour, Crisco and salt with pastry blender or by hand. Beat with flour mixture with fork until mixture forms a ball.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage, drain well.
Add other ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.
Garnish with parsley or ripe olives.

title: black bottom cups
directions: Combine cream cheese, unbeaten egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt and mix well.
Stir chocolate chips into the cream cheese mixture.
In another bowl, sift the following together: flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add the remaining ingredients to the flour mixture.
Fill 24 muffin cups one-third full with the chocolate batter.
Top each one with a heaping teaspoonful of the cream cheese mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen raspberries and applesauce; mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate and let set.
Melt 4 cups miniature marshmallows in 1/2 cup hot milk in double boiler.
Cool and blend.
Spread on top of salad and put back in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: mexicali pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in heavy 10-inch skillet over moderate heat; add onion, green pepper and red pepper and cook, uncovered, about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, corn and marjoram; raise the heat to high and cook, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Transfer to ungreased shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole or 9-inch pie plate.

title: quick pizza snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove dough from can in rolled sections; do not unroll.
Cut each roll into 12 slices; place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spoon about 1 teaspoon sauce on top of each slice; sprinkle cheese over sauce.
Return to oven; bake 3 to 5 additional minutes or until edges are brown and cheese is melted.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix and serve as dip with any fruit.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake as custard pie.
Bake at 325° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Microwave Directions:
In a quart microwave-safe casserole, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover with microwave-safe waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes or until hot, stirring twice during cooking.
Serve immediately with crackers and fresh vegetable dippers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: fu man chew
directions: Put the oil in a big skillet.
In it saute for
5 minutes the onions and celery. Add the ground beef. When beef is brown, add the soup, rice, bean sprouts with liquid, water chestnuts, soy sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a big casserole dish and bake it, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add the peas.
Stir them in and top it all with the noodles. Bake it, uncovered, for another 30 minutes at the same temperature.
Makes 10 servings.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into hot greased pan. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: decorah cream porridge(decorah rommegrot)
directions: Heat cream to boiling point.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Sift flour into cream, stirring constantly.
Let simmer until butter comes to top.
Skim off the butter and add boiling hot milk, sugar and salt.
Let simmer a few minutes.
Serve hot with sugar and cinnamon and the melted butter which was drawn off earlier (should be about 1/4 cup).

title: mint tea
directions: In a large crockery pitcher, place tea bags, sugar, mint tips or mint flakes and juice of lemons with the rinds.
Pour a teapot of boiling water over this and let stand until cool.
Strain into a gallon pitcher.
Be sure to re-squeeze lemons and add enough water to make a gallon.
Serve over ice.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding with 2 cups of pineapple juice until thick. Cool; fold in fruit and refrigerate.

title: crabmeat-spinach souffle
directions: Mix flour with butter and add remaining ingredients.
Stir well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch oiled pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 12.

title: hamburger fancy
directions: Mix meat and eggs.
Soak bread in water and squeeze out moisture.
Add to meat mixture along with salt, pepper and ketchup.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Form into 12 sausage-shaped patties.
Wrap a slice of bacon around each, securing with toothpicks.
Heat shortening in a heavy skillet on top of range or in electric skillet at 375°.
Fry in hot fat, about 8 minutes or until meat is cooked through.

title: pineapple carrot salad
directions: Pour water over jello, cheese and marshmallows and dissolve well.
Chill until it congeals pretty good.
Then add drained pineapple, carrots and pecans.
Whip 1 cup of cream or 1 package Dream Whip and fold into mixture.
Chill.
(I usually use the drained pineapple juice as part of my 2 cups of water.)

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
In medium casserole dish, layer hamburger, Tater Tots, then cheese.
Mix soup and milk; pour over casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: soy and lemon chicken
directions: Cover the bottom of pan with cooking oil.
Put in chicken. After chicken is cooked, add onion and green pepper.
Add 1/4 teaspoon seasoning salt or until desired taste, then add 1 1/2 tablespoons soy sauce and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
When finished cooking, serve over noodles or rice.
Add more soy or lemon if desired.
Serves 2.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill for 30 minutes before serving. Serve with assorted fresh fruits.

title: low-fat granola spice cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and spices.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg whites and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in flour mixture, mixing until well combined.
Add cereal.
Drop by level measuring tablespoon onto baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes until edges start to turn brown.
Cool on wire racks.

title: tally ho dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients for 15 to 20 minutes with electric mixer.

title: susan's mashed potato casserole
directions: Mash the potatoes; add butter, sour cream, green onions and soup. Put in casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Cook 10 to 15 minutes at 350° or until the cheese melts.

title: mushroom toast
directions: Cut crust
from
bread;
cut each slice into triangles. Spread small amount
of soup on each triangle.
Top with small slice of bacon.
Bake
at
350° until bacon is crisp and bread is toasted.

title: easy cheeseburger
directions: Brown chuck and onion; drain.
Spread in greased plate.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick until smooth.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over meat mixture and bake at 400°, about 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: apple-cinnamon punch
directions: Heat apple juice and red hots until red hots are dissolved.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa; add to mixture.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add milk and vanilla.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Start in cold oven; bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage, drain and crumble.
Mix cheese and sausage. Sprinkle into pie shell.
Lightly beat eggs.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to eggs.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° about 45 to 50 minutes until done.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Combine drained vegetables in a large container with cover.

title: playdough
directions: We fume and spurt

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Brush each chicken with sunflower oil.
Dredge lightly in crushed stuffing mix.
Season with pepper.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn; bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until tender.
Do not overbake.

title: pumpkin gobs
directions: *Bake one to
see
if 1/2 to 1 cup of flour needs to be added.

title: million dollar pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Blend condensed milk and lemon juice, then blend with other ingredients and pour mixture into 2 graham cracker pie crusts. Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot water devil's food cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Set aside. Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and mix well. Add dry ingredients and liquids.
Mix well.
Bake cupcakes 25 to 30 minutes, layers 35 to 40 minutes and 9 x 13-inch dish 45 minutes in 375° oven, or until done.

title: easy congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into oblong container.
Chill until set.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Lightly grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Thoroughly combine dry ingredients in a heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Bring to a bubbly boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil, without stirring, to 234° (soft ball stage) or until a small amount of syrup dropped in very cold water forms a soft ball.
Bulb of candy thermometer should not rest on bottom of saucepan.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature to 110° (pan is barely warm to touch).
Beat with wooden spoon until fudge thickens and loses its gloss.
Quickly spread in buttered pan.
Cool completely.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: chili with ground turkey
directions: Brown turkey, onions and garlic in large pot. Add kidney beans and juice, tomato juice and tomato sauce. Cook 2 to 3 hours on medium low heat. Add chili powder while cooking.

title: mushroom muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Sift dry ingredients together into a bowl; make a well in the center.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to flour mixture.
Stir until just mixed.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 11 muffins.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Cook onions and sausage until brown.
Drain.
Add kraut and 2 tablespoons of bread crumbs.
Combine cream cheese, parsley, mustard, pepper and garlic salt.
Stir in kraut mixture.
Chill.

title: cherry jeweled chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper; brown lightly in butter. Cover and simmer 40 minutes or until almost tender; drain excess drippings.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, 1/2 teaspoon salt and allspice in saucepan.
Gradually add orange juice.
Cook and stir 5 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in cherries.
Pour cherry mixture over chicken.
Simmer, covered, 5 minutes longer or until chicken is tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon sauce over chicken breasts before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ham, broccoli and cheese roll
directions: Mix ham, cheese, broccoli and mustard.
Take rolls and separate them.
On an ungreased cookie sheet, place the sections in a circle with the wide ends overlapping slightly and points radiating out like an 8-point star.
There should be about 2 to 3-inch hole in the middle.
Place the mixture around the center of the star, leaving the star ends and hole uncovered.
Fold the points over and tuck them under.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until rolls are brown and center is done.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in liquid until done.
Cut into bite size pieces and put in bottom of 9x13 greased pan.
Cook broccoli (partially), drain and put on top of chicken pieces.
Combine soups and milk, heat and pour over chicken and broccoli mix.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Prepare Stove Top Stuffing Mix and spread over top of casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until top is crunchy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients but crumbs and butter.
Place in casserole dish.
Put crumbs on top, pour melted butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: banana split cake("nothing like it!")
directions: Mix the melted margarine with the graham cracker crumbs. Press into bottom of a large 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lemon cheese (cake icing)
directions: Mix and cook until thick; takes a long time.

title: out-of-this-world rolls
directions: Soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Combine eggs, shortening, sugar, softened yeast, remaining warm water, salt and 2 1/2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Cover; allow to rise until double.
Punch down and place in refrigerator overnight.
Three hours before baking, roll out as desired.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen rolls.

title: italian beef
directions: Put meat in roaster. Add chopped onion, salt and water.

Cook in 350° oven for 3 hours. Take meat out of juice; cool and slice. Add remaining ingredients to broth. Bring to a boil. Pour over meat and marinate overnight. Heat 1 to 1 1/2 hours in oven and serve. Can be served as sandwiches or on submarine rolls. Serves 12 to 14 people.

title: vinaigrette
directions: Blend well in bowl.

title: shrimp for grill
directions: Mix ingredients and marinate shrimp for 1 hour.
Barbecue shrimp on grill (2 to 3 minutes each side).
Use foil on grill or skewers.

title: clam chowder
directions: In medium pan, cook potatoes and onion for 30 minutes.
Add butter, canned milk and clams.
Cook for another 15 minutes until done.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough in pizza pan.
Bake according to directions on package.
Spread cream cheese on cooled crust.
Spread pudding on cream cheese.
Arrange fruit on top.

title: spice beets
directions: Heat first 6 ingredients to boiling.
Add beets; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until cooked, then dice. Combine and mix all ingredients, except chips, into an 8 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Add chips to top. Bake another 15 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10-inch baking pan with Pam spray.
Dip chicken in margarine; coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until tender.

title: fruited stuffed pork chops
directions: Saute onion and celery in 1/4 cup margarine until tender; remove from heat.
Add stuffing mix, mixed dried fruit and raisins; stir well and set aside.

title: kau-sheng rib (sweet and sour)
directions: Cut ribs into 1-inch pieces.
Cut broccoli stem off; steam for 1 minute.
Put ribs, wine, sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, water and pieces of ginger in large pot.
Cover.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat; stew for 20 minutes until sauce is thick.
Lay steamed broccoli on the bottom of the plate.
Place ribs with sauce on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken in bottom of casserole.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour on top of chicken.
Cover with crumbled Ritz crackers. Put margarine pats over the crackers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and hot.

title: kenny rogers cake
directions: Thoroughly mix flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add pineapple and eggs, stirring until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Allow to cool about 10 minutes.
Make icing while cake is baking.

title: sweet potato apple bake
directions: Slice cooled sweet potatoes and combine with apples, raisins and almonds in a large bowl.
Spoon in a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: seven minute mocha mousse
directions: Thaw whipped dairy topping.
Combine milk and coffee crystals. Let stand for 2 to 3 minutes or until crystals are dissolved. Stir in fudge topping.

title: sausage breakfast quiche
directions: After meat is cooked, stir in cream cheese and keep stirring until it has simmered.
Adjust oven to the degree specified on the can of rolls.
Use a flat 9 x 12 or 10 x 13 pan.
Roll out 1 to 2 cans of crescent rolls and cover the bottom of the pan, making sure that no holes are open.
Spread meat and cheese mixture on top of rolls and then use the remaining can(s) of rolls to cover the top.
Bake according to instructions on the can or until medium brown.

title: german-chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Mix coconut and pecans together in a bowl.
Spread into bottom of pan.
Make German chocolate cake according to directions on box.
Spread over coconut and nuts.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter. Spoon over cake mix and swirl through mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Yield:
1 cake.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Add warm water; boil until tender with mustard and salt.
Drain, saving liquid.
Put in casserole dish or roaster.
Add brown sugar, sour cream and bacon. Bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 350°.
If beans look dry, add some of the liquid, drained off, after boiling.
Makes 6 servings.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Combine egg, onion, milk, oats and seasonings.
Blend and add meat; mix well.
Pack into a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: honey nuggets
directions: Mix together shortening, eggs, honey and brown sugar.
Stir together flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and add to honey mixture.
Add vanilla, walnuts and dates.
Stir in.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 120 cookies.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.

title: chicken & pasta with creamy garlic sauce
directions: Slice chicken breasts to 1-1/4 inch slices and saute in olive oil.
Remove from pan and cover to keep warm.
Cook minced onion and garlic slowly until soft.
Add celery flakes, basil, paprika, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper, sour cream and Tabasco and thicken over low heat.
Add more sour cream or milk if sauce becomes too thick.
Return chicken to pan to heat through.

title: pina colada pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk and whipped topping.
Beat with electric mixer on low until moistened.
Beat on high until thickened.
Fold in undrained pineapple.
Spoon pudding into dessert dishes. Sprinkle with coconut.
Chill well.
Makes 6 servings.
Contains 100 calories per serving.
Low calories!
Serves 6.

title: salsa ranch dip
directions: Mix packet of dip mix and sour cream. Add salsa and stir until well blended. Serve with chips.

title: german potato salad
directions: Make gravy of bacon fat and flour; then add sugar, salt, pepper, water and vinegar.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour gravy mixture over potatoes.
Serve hot.

title: homemade banana ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into freezer.
Fill rest of the way with milk.

title: pork chop scallop
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Grease 10-inch skillet with the fat.
Brown chops on both sides; season with salt and pepper. Remove chops from skillet.
Empty potatoes and packet of seasoned sauce mix into skillet.
Stir in amounts of water and milk called for on package.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions on box. Set aside.
Place a layer of coconut in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Top coconut with a layer of nuts.
Pour cake mix over top of coconut and nuts.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and butter. Add enough milk to make mixture thin enough to run.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana coconut bread
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, eggs and bananas until creamy.
Add soda, salt and flour.
Mix nuts and coconut; add to mixture. Blend well.
Pour into well-greased 4 x 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: raspberry cooler
directions: In punch bowl or large pitcher, combine raspberry juice, lemonade and water.
Stir.
Gently add ginger ale.
Garnish with lots of ice.

title: raspberry-almond coffee cake
directions: Beat butter about 2 minutes or until creamy.
Gradually add sugar,
beating
for
to
7 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time. Stir
in
almond extract.
Combine flour, baking powder and
salt; add to butter mixture alternately with sour cream. Mix at low speed, just until blended.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured loaf or regular pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: 4 step chocolate cake
directions: Blend butter and flour until creamy; add nuts.
Pour dough into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: elegant chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute mushrooms in 3 tablespoons of butter for 5 minutes. Blend in flour and salt.
Add stock and stir until thick.
Add chicken.
Cover and heat to steaming.
Mix 2 tablespoons of butter with egg yolks, onion and lemon juices, paprika and pepper.
Stir this mixture slowly into chicken and cook until thick.
Add olives, pimentos and sherry.
Serve over hot spaghetti and sprinkle with grated cheese on top.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: grilled vegetable trio
directions: Tear off a length of aluminum foil.
Place onion in center of foil in single layer.
Top with zucchini, cheese, seasonings and butter.
Bring four corners of foil up together in pyramid shape. Fold openings together loosely for heat circulation and expansion. Seal by folding over ends and pressing to package.
Grill over medium hot coals 20 minutes.
Carefully open bundle; add tomatoes. Re-seal.
Grill 20 to 30 minutes longer or until zucchini is tender and tomatoes are heated through.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Cream 1 stick
butter
and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix flour and baking powder with milk and vanilla.
Melt remaining stick of butter in a
x	9-inch	pan.
Cover surface of pan with brown sugar.
Place
pineapple
slices on top of sugar.
Put a maraschino cherry in
each hole of pineapple.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, or until a toothpick comes out dry.
Remove cake from oven. Turn upside down on a flat surface.

title: nutty cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°, grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir together dry cake mix, melted margarine and chopped nuts until well mixed.
Press mixture into bottom of pan.
Stir together brown sugar and cream cheese until well mixed.
Spread evenly over the mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans or walnuts. Bake 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a large bowl mix shortening and peanut butter. Add sugars and stir until creamy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
In another bowl combine flour, soda and salt.
Stir flour mixture into peanut butter mixture; stir well.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Crisscross with fork (dip tines in flour).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: jennifer's favorite hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion, hamburger meat, garlic, flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Stir until meat is done.
Add soup and simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in cold sour cream, mixing well.
Serve on egg noodles or rice.

title: syrup pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Pour in 8 inch pie pan.
Dot with bits of butter and nuts.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour. Makes 6-8 servings.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until it boils and sugar melts completely.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Add corn flakes.
Roll into balls and place on wax paper.

title: grandma titrud's molasses cake
directions: Place 1/2 cup shortening in a 1 cup measure and fill cup with boiling water.
Place 2/3 cup molasses in a 1 cup measure and fill cup with white sugar.
Dissolve soda in warm water.
Mix flour, ginger, cloves and cinnamon.
Add to mixture.
Last, add the well beaten eggs.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a very quick oven (375°) for 20 to 25 minutes, until done.

title: sugar-free strawberry or raspberry pie
directions: Prepare the filling before preparing the crust in this recipe. Put the first 4 ingredients into blender on high, half minute or until thoroughly combined.
Pour into a 2-quart saucepan, cooking and stirring constantly on high heat, with wire whisk, until comes to a boil (about 4 to 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in frozen berries.
Allow to cool while preparing pie shell.

title: strawberry-grape slush
directions: Take one cup of washed, chopped strawberries and blend on low with grape juice.
Add crushed ice and puree until smooth and creamy.
Pour into tall glass and enjoy.

title: italian bean soup
directions: Put beans in water; boil 2 minutes.
Remove; cover and let stand 1 hour.
Add garlic, onion, carrots, celery, tomatoes and ham.
Bring mix to boil; reduce to simmer and cover.
Cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours until beans mash easily.
Remove ham bone.
Coarsely chop ham and blend 1/2 of soup mix until smooth.
Add to rest of soup and ham.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes over medium heat.
Top with Parmesan cheese and parsley.

title: fresh pasta
directions: Combine flour and salt in a large bowl. Combine eggs, oil and milk in a small bowl.
Pour liquid mixture into dry mixture. Knead until dough forms a smooth ball. Roll dough out thinly and cut into desired shapes.
Drop pasta into boiling salted water. Cook until al dente.
Fresh pasta cooks much quicker than dry pasta.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Put bread in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour mixture over bread and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: no bake bars
directions: Blend together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Cook over low heat until eggs are set.
Blend in the crumbs, marshmallows, coconut and pecans.
Press into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: hummel's futter
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased 7 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Crumble on a plate.
Slice bananas and oranges; sprinkle 2 tablespoons over fruit and top with whipped cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl.
Stir in oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Sift flour mixture into egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Remove from pans after cooling for 10 minutes.

title: perky potato salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl; add chilled dressing and mix thoroughly.
Garnish with paprika.
Refrigerate until time to serve.
Yields 6 servings.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add more powdered sugar as needed for candy-like consistency.
Form into balls and freeze on wax paper-lined cookie sheets until firm.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip peanut butter balls into melted chocolate using toothpicks.
Replace on cookie sheets, removing toothpicks and smoothing over toothpick holes.
Refreeze to harden chocolate. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil sugar and cream until it forms soft ball in cool water. Takes about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add peanut butter.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: chipped beef log
directions: Put cream cheese in microwave for a minute or until soft. Stir the cream cheese until creamy and then add horseradish and scallions.
Open the dried beef.
Save 10 or 12 of the outside slices.
Tear the remaining dried beef and add to cream cheese mixture.
Place the reserved pieces of beef on plastic wrap. Form a base, approximately 3 x 12 inches for the log.
Put the cream cheese mixture on the beef to form a log.
Cover with the rest of the beef.
Roll into a log.
Refrigerate for 24 to 48 hours.
Serves about 20.
Serve on mini bagels or Triscuits. Leftovers will freeze for a month if wrapped tightly.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a saucepan, blend butter and sugar; heat to boiling point.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes. Add pecans.
Put crackers on ungreased cookie sheet. Spread sugar mixture over crackers.
Bake 5 minutes and cut in strips while warm. Store in airtight container.

title: angel jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups hot water.
Add 2 cups strawberries. When Jell-O and strawberries begin to thicken, fold in Cool Whip. Crumble angel food cake in chunks into bowl.
Pour Jell-O, strawberry and Cool Whip mixture over cake.
Make sure to work down through cake.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Put all ingredients in a baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with Doritos and shredded cheese and place under broiler for another 10 minutes.

title: frozen sherbet fruit salad
directions: In a small bowl, blend sherbet until softened. Fold in remaining ingredients. Pour into 10-inch square pan. Freeze 2 hours or until firm. Cut into squares to serve.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, cream of coconut and club soda. Scoop ice cream on top.

title: possum and chestnuts
directions: Skin the possum; clean well and remove glands.
Place in large pot; cover in boiling water.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Rub with salt and pepper.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions on package.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well (I use an electric hand mixer).
Place sliced orange on top.
Chill and serve.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Cut pound cake into cubes and spread in bottom of trifle dish. Mix pudding according to directions.
Spread evenly on top of cake.
Make glaze according to directions.
Slice strawberries; add to glaze.
Spread evenly on top of pudding.
Repeat this process.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Top with strawberries.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Add egg and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough from teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Grease and flour pan(s).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Stir baking soda into sour cream and add to butter-sugar mixture. Beat well.
Stir in vanilla and mashed banana.
Sift in flour and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and pour into pan(s).
Bake 50 to 60 minutes for Bundt pan, less for mini muffins or small loaves.

title: whiskey sours
directions: Mix on high in blender.

title: citrus cooler
directions: Combine sugar and water in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour sugar mixture into a 4 1/2-quart freezer container.
Stir in fruit juices; freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer several hours before serving (mixture should be slushy).
Stir in ginger ale.
Garnish with cut fruit, if desired.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: italian cheese cake
directions: Mix pie crust ingredients together; dough will be sticky.
Put in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
If dough is still sticky, use flour.
Roll out on wax paper.
Put in pie pan and add filling. Bake for almost 1 hour at 350°.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, pudding, oil and water. Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in sour cream, chips, pecans, coconut and grated chocolate.
Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan and bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Dice zucchini and cook in salted water until tender.
Drain and let cool.
Mix eggs, baking powder, flour, milk, parsley, chilies and cheese together.
Fold in cooled zucchini.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour in a slow oven, 300°.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat oleo until soft.
Add sugar and blend until creamy.
Add vanilla and flour; stir in pecans.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on greased sheet at 300° for 45 minutes.
While hot, roll in confectioners sugar.
Roll again when cool.
Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all together and let marinate in refrigerator overnight. Serve as a dip with tortilla chips.

title: carbanari
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Cut up bacon and saute in separate small pan. Cook linguini al dente.
Have all cooking at the same time.
Mix parsley and grated cheese with the 2 eggs in a bowl and let stand.
When linguini is cooked, drain but don't wash.
Into the hot pot place the parsley, grated cheese and eggs.
Place the linguini on top and mix, this will cook the eggs.
Pour the sauteed onion and butter on top and the sauteed bacon with the grease on top of the linguini and mix well.
Serve immediately since it is not as tasty cold.

title: teresa's buttermilk buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix with buttermilk and sugar.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Add butter and eggs.
Add 4 cups flour, soda and salt; beat well.
Then add remaining flour.
Knead well.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and shape into rolls. Let rise again.
Bake at 400° for about 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: yankee salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: layered salad
directions: *Thaw to 2 cups; not cooked.

title: chicken pie
directions: Put chicken in large baking dish.
Melt margarine and pour over chicken.
Add salt and pepper.
Blend together the flour and milk.
Spread over chicken.
Blend soup and broth; pour over flour mixture. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 425°.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk in a large bowl and beat until smooth and thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Stir until well blended.

title: for children:  home made play dough
directions: Boil the water.
Remove from heat and add salt, powdered alum and food coloring.
Stir until salt is dissolved.
While still hot, add oil and flour.
Stir and then remove from pan and knead until smooth and soft.

title: hot bean and potato salad(serve with meat or fish)
directions: Cook bacon in skillet over medium heat until crisp.
Drain on paper towels; crumble and reserve.
Discard all but 1 tablespoon bacon fat.
Add onion and garlic; stirring occasionally, cook until golden, about 3 minutes.
Stir in potatoes and water; season with salt.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add beans; cover and cook 8 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.
Drain any liquid.
Sprinkle with salad dressing and bacon.
Toss gently. Makes 4 servings.
Per serving:
236 calories, 6 g protein, 26 g carbohydrate, 13 g fat, 7 mg cholesterol and 656 mg sodium.

title: cheese-bacon omelet
directions: A snap in an electric skillet.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes. Boil them until done, but don't overcook. Cool. Peel and cut into bite size pieces. Combine in another bowl the Miracle Whip, lemon juice, mustard, salt and pepper. Stir and then add diced onions, celery and green peppers. Pour over potatoes. Add diced ham and cheese and gently stir.

title: garden vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, saut the carrots, onions and garlic over low heat until softened, about 5 minutes. Add broth, cabbage, beans, tomato paste, oregano and salt. Bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer, covered, about 15 minutes or until beans are tender. Stir in zucchini and heat 3 to 4 minutes. Serve hot.

title: mama's prune cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Beat well and stir in prunes and nuts.
Add vanilla.
Pour into two 9-inch cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: maple milk shake
directions: Place ice cream, milk and syrup in a mixer bowl.
Beat with electric mixer.
Serves 8.
Serve cold.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine chopped broccoli with chicken stock and boil until tender.
In saucepan, saute ham and onions until onions are transparent.
Add ham and onions to soup.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling water containing diced potatoes.
Cook about 10 minutes.

title: anzac biscuits(cookies)
directions: *May substitute honey or molasses.

title: party pinwheels
directions: Spread ham with softened cream cheese.
Roll around pickle and chill.
Then slice crosswise and serve.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Cook chicken in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Place in dish skin side down to cook.
Turn chicken over; sprinkle with spices. Bake 20 minutes more.
Combine soup and wine.
Pour over chicken. Bake 20 minutes more (covered).
Serve over cooked rice.

title: german sausage in sauce
directions: Cut up the sausage and precook in oven.
Drain off excess grease and put in large cooking pot.
Add all other ingredients and spices and simmer for several hours before serving.

title: cheese chips
directions: To remove grease from collars, rub in a little cheap shampoo, then sprinkle collar with baking soda.
Wash in machine.

title: vegetable bread
directions: Press dough on greased cookie sheet.
Add remaining ingredients in layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and parsley.
Cut 1-inch wide strips along sides of dough. Close loaf by folding sides up alternating sides.
Wash with beaten egg.
Let rise 1/2 hour or until double in size or until you're ready to bake.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, eggs and Crisco together.
Add salt, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, vanilla and pumpkin; mix together. Add flour and mix (if mixture is runny, add more flour).
Add chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: plucking cake
directions: Melt margarine and mix with sugar, cinnamon, nuts and nutmeg. Pull or cut biscuits into quarters and place half in Bundt pan. Place half of sugar mixture and raisins.
Drop in remaining biscuits and top with remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn out while hot.

title: frosted mandarin dessert
directions: Drain oranges, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add measured liquid.
Add sherbet by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in oranges.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.
Makes about 5 cups (8 servings).

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread ingredients in order given so that you start with cream cheese on the bottom of glass Pyrex dish.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, until bubbly.
Enjoy!

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Melt margarine in 1 cup water in saucepan.
Remove from heat. Combine with stuffing mix in large bowl, mixing well.
Chill.
Add remaining ingredients except bacon, mixing well.
Shape into pecan-shaped balls.
Wrap with bacon and secure with toothpicks. Place into baking dish and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: chicken and dried beef casserole
directions: Roll up chicken pieces.
Take slices of bacon and wrap around chicken; hook with toothpicks.
Butter 10 x 10 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Line with dried beef.
Place chicken on top of beef.
Mix mushroom soup with sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 350°.
Remove foil and brown about 30 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix up good.
Make into a little ball.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° about 1 minute.
Real good.

title: cheesy crab dip
directions: Drain crabmeat, if can is used.

title: tuna-mac casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; let stand for 1 hour.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in a 2-quart baking dish.

title: golden sun salad
directions: Steam squash and rutabaga 2 minutes; slice fruit.
For dressing, puree mango, vinegar and curry in blender.
Mix all together, except cabbage.
Shred cabbage.
Serve mixture on cabbage.

title: cinnamon thumbs
directions: Roll into balls (size of walnut).
Push thumb into center flattening some.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While hot roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture (1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon).

title: my best zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla. Blend together.
Stir in squash.
Sift dry ingredients and blend into creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tested done.

title: pizza soup
directions: In large saucepan, saute mushrooms and onion in oil for 2-3 minutes or until tender. Add water, pizza sauce, pepperoni, tomatoes, sausage and Italian seasoning. Bring to boil over medium heat. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Before serving, stir in Parmesan cheese. Garnish with mozzarella cheese.
